animal.description:
Midnight Lee is 2 years and 45lbs. We pulled him from a neighboring county facility on 11/7.

"This handsome little guy is Midnight Lee; AKA your new BFF! Midnight Lee is 45 pounds of pure snuggles, wanting nothing more than your cuddles, love, and attention - oh, and plenty of toys! He is around 2 years old, house trained, has good leash manners, and does well with other dogs. Midnight Lee is still learning a few basic commands (sit, down, stay, quiet etc.) and how to like his crate, but is responding to training well as he is very intelligent and treat motivated. Midnight Lee asks that you introduce him to new places and people slowly. He does tend to get a little overwhelmed at first, but once he gets comfortable, he's back to being his normal, silly self. Let's get this sweetheart adopted!"

Midnight Lee has a secret obsession ... he loves toys and is an excellent demolition man for breaking down cardboard. He is perfectly happy rolling about in the toys he has conquered.

This handsome boy will require someone to teach him the ropes of living in a home. He would love someone who can give him undivided attention at times, as he loves to lay in your lap for snuggles and calm petting.

This gorgeous boy is Midnight Lee and he really is as sweet as he can be! He would like nothing more than to ring in the new year with a new family. Be prepared for lots of snuggles as this boy is a lap dog who loves for you to shower him with attention. Midnight Lee is around two years old and has good leash manners. Please help spread the word, let's get this sweetheart a home!

Inquiries: adoptions@plannedpethoodrockymount.com
Adoption Application Link: https://www.plannedpethoodrockymount.com/adoptions

Click here to view our general adoption fees. Our adoption fees help to provide a portion of the care that we provide our animals.

Prior to adoption, all of our animals are altered, vaccinated, microchipped, tested for heartworm (dogs), and placed on a monthly preventative, in addition to other necessary treatments.

Adoption Center Hours:
Tuesday - Friday:: 12-6p.m.
Saturday:: 11-4p.m.

At FCHS, we commit to our animals; for this reason, all of our animals have a lifetime commitment from us. If an adoption does not work out, for any reason, we ask that all FCHS animals be returned to our facility.

Gemma von Gerbstedt is a beautiful 2-year-old German Shepherd.  Outgoing and confident, this girl has a wonderful medium energy level and loves going for walks (she might pull a little to let you know how excited she is, but only if you let her take charge)!  She can be incredibly affectionate with her people – she has made many human friends at the rescue and is quick to ask for some much-loved petting.  She needs some help with her doggy socializing, but she’s working very hard at the rescue!  She can be pushy at first in playgroup, but she takes corrections well and avoids confrontation.  She wants to be a playful pup – she just needs a firm hand to teach her how to behave.  If you’re looking for a loving gal and ready to put in the time to help her learn her doggy manners, Gemma is ready to meet you!

animal.description:
Duke von Dettelbach is a very handsome 11-12 month old Shepherd mix. This young cutie with the dark eyes and tidy, spotty coat has come so far in his short time at the rescue, he's now a happy and outgoing boy with people and other pups. Duke throws himself into everything, including onto your lap if he can. He gets excited about getting out and will jet out ahead, but he’s getting good about listening to direction, especially if you are consistent. His spirited nature also extends to his interactions with other dogs.  He can come on a bit strong for some but, with the right equally playful partner he'll happily play and play. He is adorable, loves fun and is great company. For that reason he’s looking for a home that will add experiences and adventure with boundaries and structure. Duke has flourished with the security, guidance and routine at the rescue. He is looking for a cat-free home please.

animal.description:
To make the adoption process faster and easier, please visit www.almosthomeohio.org and complete our online application!
Dogs posted are currently up for adoption unless otherwise noted. Our goal is to match dogs with a suitable home/family so that at any time, dogs shown here may already have a potential match. We post dogs as quickly as possible however there may be some not yet pictured. We allow our dogs time to settle in with their foster families so that we can evaluate their health and personality.

Meet Buddy, our 3-year old collie who is blind, but does not seem to regard this as a disability. He quickly mapped the home where he is living and now only occasionally bumps into anything. He has also mapped his outdoor yard and requires a fenced in yard for safety. When he is outside, he feels secure and explores now that he knows where the fence is.

Buddy loves his people but also enjoys the other dogs in the household. He would enjoy a companion dog as long as it were not too boisterous since he cannot see. He is mellow and relaxed and understands "sit," "shake," his name, and comes when he is called. He views his crate as a safe spot and is only put there with the gate closed when the family is gone or when they go to bed, both for his safety. He hasn't been around kids but does fine with cats. He is house trained, rides well in the car but does some drooling when it is moving. His hearing is sensitive, understandably, so he is not fond of loud noises like thunder and fireworks and squeaky toys scare him but doesn't mind household noises like the vacuum cleaner. When meeting new people, he is a little shy at first but quickly warms up to them. He does know what he wants and is not shy about going for it. Once when he wanted to reach his crate and it was not time for bed, he crawled through the cat gate to get there. Another time he managed to find a bone which was bought for him, at the bottom of a grocery sack. He took the plastic off and started gnawing at it without damaging any of the other packages.

Dogs who are blind need homes where things are kept in the same location so they can be secure as they navigate. He shows a strong dislike of concrete, refusing to walk on it, and if he has to, he trembles, but has no trouble with linoleum. He quickly learned to manage the 4 steps on and off the deck. His foster mom tells him "step up" or "step down" as he approaches them but he does not use a full staircase. He is a lovable, smart dog, who is ready to curl up beside you in his forever home. As with other dogs who are blind, Buddy needs a home where the family is experienced with dogs who are blind or willing to get training to help him live to the fullest. The adoption fee for Buddy is $300Dont forget to visit our informative website, www.almosthomeohio.org, for valuable information and interesting features. 1/25/21 5:18 PM

animal.description:
Hera 

Im Hera, Im a 2 year old GSD mix and I have lived the life no dog should have to. 

I came by plane to this rescue from a life I would rather forget about, but I am so happy to have been saved and me and my 2 babies were given the opportunity to live great lives. I however.... wasn't too sure about humans and had little to no trust in them, infact... my foster mom thinks I may have been feral for quite some time, but now after spending more time with me she thinks that that is only partially true. Humans have clearly shown me evil, and have hurt me to the point where I have no trust for strangers. 

It has taken me close to 3 months of being with my foster family to realize that I can start being a real dog. I have opened up and have started to trust my foster mama little by little, but it has taken me time, love, and patience. She is so so great though... and I have even been giving her kisses. I'm REALLY liking how it feels to be loved!

I am not a dog that you can throw into chaos, and I prefer to take baby steps while learning how to be a dog and part of a family. If I am put into an uncomfortable or unfamiliar situation I will shut down, and roll like a little alligator and try to run away... because that's all I know, fight or flight. I also prefer women to men so it's very important that a woman who is kind natured by in the home with me.

Although I have connected with one main woman in the home I'm in now, I have done better and better with the other men and women living in the house. What I love the MOST you ask.... OTHER DOGS! I am LOVING the ability to play with other dogs!! Wow, how fun!!! So it is VERY important in my new home that another playful, submissive and kind dog be present as this will greatly help with my confidence and teach me how to be the best girl and family member. On the flip side though, I need a home without children, adults only please!

My foster family though is helping me in different situations, meeting new people and exposing me to things that may be scary... but learning that I can be safe and happy.

 

 

Ideally whoever wants to adopt Hera will need to understand that this is going to be a lifetime commitment, and she may never fully come out of her shell due to how much evil she has been shown by people. 

BUT she does have the potential to come out of her shell and love again. It is just going to take an incredibly special soul to help mend hers. 

She doesnt mind the cats at all, and is crate trained. 

 

Hera really is such an amazing dog with a beautiful soul, she just needs the right person to show her that. To love her, and to give her the gift of patience while she learns that the world is not the awful place she has been shown it is for the last two years. We would want to start with a foster to adopt situation ideally as she is going to need someone to invest a lot of time into her, and if it isnt the right fit wed like her to come back here instead of being passed around. 

She has so much potential, and we really believe she will be a good dog for the right person. 

 

If you are interested in adopting, please visit our website and complete an adoption application at www.elpasocountycanine.org/available-dogs

I'm Miko and I am SO GLAD to be here in Colorado because I am ready for ADVENTURE! I'm a 4-year-old Shepherd mix, and I weigh about 50 pounds. My very favorite thing in the world is to be out exploring - whether it's a walk around the neighborhood, or a hiking trail, I love being out and moving. I would definitely have the stamina to accompany you on a long day hike, or even a long run (after I finish my heartworm treatment that the rescue is going to take care of for me!). Now, I probably didn't spend a lot of time inside in my past, and while I LOVE people of all sizes, I was never taught not to play with them without using my mouth, so I will need some training on that, as well as some basic house manners and obedience. I'd probably do best in a home with no kids, or at least older kids who can help me learn the right way to play. I'm house trained and crate trained, and I love to snuggle up with you on the couch at night. Because of my high prey drive, I'd likely do better in a home without cats. Please come meet me and let's talk about what kind of adventures we can take together!

Miko is neutered, up-to-date on vaccinations, microchipped and will be undergoing heartworm treatment at the full expense of the rescue. Please do not delay in completing an application to have Miko become a member of your family today!

animal.description:
Well hello there folks! My name is Little Debbie. I’m a 2 year old who was found as a stray and brought to animal control. I’m sure many of you have seen my photos and videos and thought, “Oh that poor thing. She must be suffering with those legs!” 
Well let me tell you how wrong you are. Yes, my rear legs are deformed and are angled at 90 degrees, and my front legs are bowed out, but that doesn’t slow me down one bit. In fact, if you don’t watch out, I’ll go scooting past you so fast your head will spin! Now I can’t take stairs, but luckily I only weigh 28 pounds and my foster parents carry me out to do my business, or to put me on the couch with them so I can snuggle! 
And let me tell you I love to snuggle! If you cradle me like a baby and stroke my belly I’ll purr like a kitten! Speaking of kittens, I am very intrigued by the cat who lives in my foster house. I look at her with my big eyes and listen with these great ears. I don’t miss a thing in this house, and if they would let me, I’d probably chase that cat! I’m also very interested in my foster brother & sister and I think I would do fine with other dogs. 
Now I mentioned before that my foster parents carry me out to do my business. I know that I’m supposed to go outside but I’m not perfect yet and I do have some accidents. But I look at them with my big eyes and their heart melts and so will yours if you adopt me. I’ve been spayed and I’m perfectly healthy except for my legs which are going to be evaluated to see if physical therapy will help. I have a very healthy appetite and love treats! I will also let you know when I want attention with a throaty growl which makes my foster Dad laugh because it comes out of this little body!
So, if you’re looking for a feisty, loving, snuggling bully who just needs a little extra TLC, I am your girl! Love to all!


If you would like to donate to Little Debbie's care, please go to our website at http://shopcebr.com/products/donation.


HOW TO QUALIFY FOR A CEBR BULLY To determine if you qualify to adopt one of our adorable bullies start by viewing our Adoption Area Map. If you fall within the boundaries and are interested in our bullies the first step is to complete an application by visiting www.ebullymatch.com

animal.description:
NAME: River
BREED: Shepherd/Pit Bull Mix
BIRTHDAY: 2012

There is never a day when we don't get requests to help dogs. Not one, not two, but literally dozens of emails and messages. Every. Single. Day. We are the smallest rescue ever, so we have to say "no" over and over and over. It's never easy, but some cases are harder than others, and some stories and faces stick with us more than others. Such is the case with River, a sweet and loving girl in South Carolina. A volunteer reached out to us, desperate and dedicated to help River find a rescue or forever home before she has to spend yet another winter on the concrete floor of the shelter. This will be River's FIFTH winter in the pound: she has lived there since she was three years old, and as a mature lady of eight she is now even less adoptable.

So why is River still in the shelter, after so many years? There are two reasons, one negative and one positive. This poor girl has a lot working against her- she's not young, she's a bully mix, she's dog-selective and dominant, she chases cats, and she has "degenerative joint disease in her back knees, luxating patellas, and a torn ACL that has reattached with scar tissue" (per the shelter vet's diagnosis). But let's think about it this way... after five years, this mess of a dog is still alive in a SC pound... and it's because she's an awesome dog. So here's the positive, which has kept her from euthanasia: River is a NICE dog, friendly and happy to meet new people. She loves to play any chance she gets, and although she doesn't love all dogs she is friendly enough to have a kennel mate. Most young dogs would deteriorate mentally after being cooped up for so long, but not River- her bright spirit has sustained her and kept her tolerant and manageable despite unfavorable living conditions. She's a fighter and a survivor, and she deserves some attention and some HELP!

We'd love to take River, but with so many dogs and cats here it's just not a good fit here. So we need YOU to help us! Please spread the word far and wide, with people and rescues who may have a spot to squeeze in just one more good dog. Transportation is available to anywhere River needs to go, and any medical expenses will be covered by very generous volunteers from the shelter. Personally we wouldn't do much more than good pain meds for those old legs, but if a vet recommends surgery that will be covered as well. There's nothing to lose and everything to gain by helping the helpless- please take a minute to help River!

For more information please email GoodOldTails@gmail.com

animal.description:
Still Needing work and may never be a cuddle dog. 
Pamela came to us shaking in a corner and wouldn't move. Any space open she found a small corner to hide in. She was at the county shelter where she had no change and we were her last hope. Pamela has since come out of her shell in many areas. She's very excited about her outdoor time and has started jumping on me to get her leash on (big step). Sometimes if I'm not quick enough I have to wait for her to come back over to me again to get her leash on. She's highly intelligent and has learned many basic words like, come on and crate, let's go. From the first day I met her I knew how smart she was. The way she tilts her head trying to understand me when I'm talking to her. I thought I was in trouble with this one. The first day was rocky. I made the mistake of letting her freeroam in the house and all it did was scare her and it took a couple of us to get her out from behind the washer. After a few days though, she started coming around. I'd make her go out on the leash to potty. She'd do a stop and go jester. Stop and jump forward, stop, and jump forward. eventually, she figured out where we were going and was first out the door. She's now going out with 3 to 4 other dogs on potty breaks in the play yard and as long as I keep to the structure she's perfectly fine.     
The other day I tried to allow a stranger (volunteer) to take her out in another direction for a potty break and she didn't understand and fought against it and that is what made me decide she was ready for adoption. I believe she can bond with her people but will always be fearful of strangers. She needs you, if you've read this so far then you are probably just that person to give her the love and time to bond with. I'm a rescuer, I rehabilitate dogs like this all the time and there's more out there that need me. So it's time for Pamela to go to her person. Her people that can give her, her forever. She certainly has the potential to bond, especially if you have food. She's ready and I will help you help her. 
Please consider Pamela 

Get your applications in!
https://www.causendogrescue.org/adoption-application.html 

We only do meet and greets for approved applications.

Adoption fee is $250.

All dogs will be Up-to-date on Shots, worming, Spayed/Neutered and Microchipped.   We will also do random, periodic vet checks to ensure all dogs adopted from us continue to have the best care.  We will check for any follow up visits needed and that they are on a monthly Heartworm Prevention.

If you rent or own a home, we prefer you to have a fenced in yard. 

Apartment living is also ok but prefer a fenced in area if close to the road.
All adults in the home will need to know they are getting a dog and will need to sign the adoption agreement.
We do not adopt to college students with multiple roommates. 
Military will need to provide a backup plan.
We require all pets in the home to be spay and/or neutered. Because too many dogs are being killed, due to there not being enough homes per dog in need. Only the lucky ones end up here.

animal.description:
Big Red's stats:
Potty trained - YES
Kennel trained - YES
Destructive when left at home - NEVER
Walks like a good dog on leash - YES
Respectful kiddos 10 years and older - YES
Dogs bigger than her, preferably males - YES
Knows her name - YES
Featured in our Heroes & Hounds 2021 calendar - OH YOU BETCHA YES!

These are some of the qualities that make Big Red such a great catch! Young munchkin kiddos, kitties, and tiny fluffy dogs are not a suitable match for her, but look at all the other types of homes she could get along with! She can tolerate little kids in small doses, but not 24/7. Big Red has thrived in our play group sessions, when she finds the right dogs to jive with! Big Red sadly has been adopted and returned twice now, and she is looking for her perfect match. It's been a bit of trial and error finding that match, but we are confident there is the right family out there for Big Red. She's a beautiful girl with a striking red coat color. She has a sweet and gentle demeanor and loves to match your energy - you want to go for a long walk? Let's go! Want to chill on the couch in the AC for a bit? Game on!
Where ever life takes you, think of how Big Red could be right at your side, your faithful companion. All you need to do is apply now and schedule your adoption visit!

animal.description:
AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION IN SOUTH CAROLINA OR VERMONT AREA

Meet Mikey! Here is a video in Vermont:

https://youtu.be/53WMwnM0Gc4

Mikey is 2 1/2 years old (approx. DOB 3-16-18), male, 30 lbs., vetted, is or will be neutered, and micro-chipped

Mikey is the sweetest, happiest, most loving boy. He's a dapper, dandy and handsome dude! He's approximately 4 years old and 30 lbs, fully vetted, heart worm neg and neutered.

Mikey is high energy and looking for an active guardian who will take him places and keep him entertained and experiencing life. His person needs to be dog savvy and able to "read" what Mikey has to say.

Mikey needs...

An active life style,

A home with a fenced yard,

No small/young children,

Best to be paired with a well balanced female dog,

A dog savvy person, willing to help Mikey transition to a new home.

Mikey's accomplishments...

Walks well on leash and loves to go,

Learning to ride calmly in a car either with a bully stick to chew or with the window cracked (while tethered) so he can look out and smell the roses,

Crate trained and does well with enough exercise and a Kong or chew,

Sleeps through the night,

Is not a nuisance barker.

Mikey is currently in a foster home with 3 medium sized females. He is walked daily, is learning house manners and training, how to calmly sit and wait before coming through a doorway or getting in and out of the car. He has to sit, stay and look his foster mom in the eye before his food bowl is placed on the ground. Watching him learn to TEAR his eyes away from the bowl in order to be fed was hysterical! He likes hanging in the yard, lying in the sun and leaps as he chases his ball.

Mikey will be man or woman's best friend if given a bit of time to trust, adapt and settle in.

He's a Passion 4 Paws rescue who is available for adoption, foster to adopt or foster in Upstate SC and surrounding area.

Stay tuned for more information as Mikey is a new rescue!

If you are interested in adopting Mikey please fill out an Application at

www.Passion-4-Paws.org

(please make sure you have the Vermont site not CT) - thanks!

Please note Fosters have 1st option of Adoption.

Check out his Facebook page (please "Like" us while you are there)!

Disclosure:

Breed labels are often incorrect: we rarely know the genetic lineage of the dogs we rescue. Many shelters and rescues specify breeds based on appearance; however, research has shown that less than 2% of a dog's DNA determines appearance!

Passion 4 Paws does not practice the use of labels pertaining to compatibility with others or dog breed. Labels such as "dog friendly" and "child friendly" should be used with caution as they often over-simplify the personalities and behavior of dogs.

animal.description: You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Gabby and Gigi (AL) are bonded female Chihuahua mixes rescued from an Alabama kill-shelter, where - scared and shy - they clung together for comfort. Their bond is very strong and they must be adopted together. They are both approximately 25 lbs and Gabby is estimated to be 4 years old, while Gigi is thought to be 5-6 years. With their terrifying shelter experience behind them and a little TLC, they are now blossoming and the lucky family who adopts them can count on a double dose of daily joy! Their foster mom says they are charming, playful and ridiculously affectionate. They are very social with people once they get to know you, and they like other dogs and even cats, with proper introductions. They need space (inside and outside) to run around and play. They follow their person around like ducklings, because they want to be your everything, so they will do best with someone who is home for the most part. Their favorite position is snuggling with each other, preferably on top of a human, for hours! If you have room in your heart and your home for these two delightful characters, please apply to adopt at www.rescuedogsrocknyc.org.

ALL PETS AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION ONLY TO RESIDENTS OF THE DALLAS/FT WORTH METROPLEX

MEET AND GREET APPOINTMENTS SET UP WITH PRE-APPROVED APPLICATION ONLY

Leto is one special girl! We rescued her with her five puppies from a very high kill small shelter in South TX. She was so emaciated and had trouble breathing. Once she arrived we did an X-ray only to discover at some point all the bones in her throat were crushed and basically didn’t exist any more. It’s like her throat is a pocket that catches air ... you will understand when you hear her ? snore. She is a happy girl and her snoring doesn’t bother her at all! 

She is an angel on earth... so gentle, loving, and sweet. She loves to play fetch and carry any toy she can find around in her mouth. She is great with kids, dogs, and cats. She is so deserving of a forever family and we know once she finds them they will love her as much as we do ??

If you would like to meet Leto, the first step in the process is to complete an application.  Please go to roadtrip4paws.com and click on the Adopt tab to find a link to our online application.  

Home visits required for all dog adoptions

We reserve the right to refuse placement of an animal for any reason

animal.description: Emmett is a graduate of  Good Dog Pet Training. He was sadly returned to us in August and picked up some unruly habits like being reactive on his walks and when people enter his home. He loves his person and bonds quickly but is fearful when new people approach. Our goal is for him to gain his confidence back and feel comfortable in his space which he has, but will need continued work on that. He will need a confident and committed owner to continue with his training and set the boundaries and structure he needs and thrives with. Trust us when we say he will not disappoint in the loyalty or loving department. He is a pro at cuddling and will enjoy the downtime with his companion. We suggest an adult only home so you can stay committed and dedicated to Emmett. His world needs to be kept small as he is not a sociable dog so a low key, low traffic home is best. He is such a good, loyal boy-we know his person is out there!

animal.description: Hi! My name is Shiloh, & I'm an 8-year old male beagle mix. I've lived all my life with Camo, who is also available for adoption. But we can be placed separately. For the 1st 6 years of my life, I spent most of my time shut in a room with Camo. Then 2 years ago, a couple moved into the house where I lived & worked really hard to socialize me. I've made major improvements! When I meet someone new, I will bark at them. But if you give me lots of soft treats, I'll warm up to you & be your best buddy! Besides Camo, I've also been around cats & I'm fine with them. (I'm dominant with other dogs). I'm basically housetrained, but if you don't let me out, then I'll go in the house. For the past 2 years, I'm used to going out several times a day, & I will whine when I need to go outside. I enjoy playing tug-of-war! I've been around children & I'm fine with them. But it's important to take your time introducing me to strangers & let me get to know them at my own pace. I'm neutered. There is a hard lump on my hip that needs to be removed ASAP. I'm in a foster home now & will have my surgery soon! Please think about making me part of your family. I love being part of a family & loved!

animal.description:
Daisey May is a 4 year old Chihuahua mix. 

When my family moved away, I was very pregnant. My foster mom had to start carrying me out to potty because I was so big and I would roll down the steps. Being pregnant was very stressful and all of my 8 puppies died.  

I was not sure about all the new things in my new home but I started to trust my foster mom and we have become inseparable.  I do have separation anxiety when my foster leaves the house. It takes me a while to warm up to new people. I bond closely with my person. I would do best in a home as an only dog and no children. 

I really need someone to be patient with me. I am a good girl and am looking for a special person who will love me forever. My foster mom cuddles me and sings me songs. I really like to do that most of all. I use a dog door. I do not use a crate and sleep in the bed. 

My adoption fee is $150 and includes up to date shots, heart worm test, microchip and spay. I can go on a home visit  with you for 1 week to see how things go! If interested in adopting Daisey Mae, send an email to adoptions.spspca@gmail.com

animal.description:
My name is Daisy and I'm a super happy, wiggle butt so it's really confusing how I ended up at the shelter.  My prior owners made me live outside 24-7 and when I got bored and hungry, I dug in the trash and the garden.  They didn't like this and took me to the shelter.  I swear I'm a good dog and it really hurt my feelings to be betrayed by my family, but I'm ready to start a happier chapter with you!  I chase squirrels, but I get along with dogs, cats and kids.   I have never met a stranger and I ride like  a lady in the car.   My foster says I'm house trained and am a mellow, sweet cuddler.  So far I'm "low maintenance" but it takes a few weeks for a dog's true personality to shine.   Don't you want my wiggle butt to welcome you after a long day?  I'm 6 years young and have so much love to give you.  

I'm heartworm positive and this is very common in Texas for dogs who are not kept on monthly heartworm prevention (it only takes one mosquito bite to infect your dog!).  The rescue is paying for my heartworm treatment and is happy to talk to you about what my recovery will entail (mostly rest!), but please don't let this stop you from applying to adopt me! 

Daisy 
Female 
Lab Mix 
6 years Old 
47 lbs 

https://nhanimalrescue.org/adoption-information/

animal.description:
Dewey and Sky are back with us in rescue. They originally came from a hoarding case in Iowa last year. Sky came to us pregnant and had 7 healthy pups who have all been adopted. Dewey and Sky were adopted in May and were wonderful guardians on their farm, enjoying what they like to do and are good at. They have been guardians for goats, sheep, llamas, chickens, and goats. Unfortunately the neighboring farm recently began shooting tannerite and the explosions scared Dewey and Sky so badly they discovered they could jump the fence. With that discovery made, they jump the 4 ft fence easily and roam all day. The neighbors that scared them threatened to shoot them, so we brought them to safety as quickly as we could. However, they are really missing their livestock and their farm. 

Dewey and Sky are 2 years old and such gentle spirits. They are wonderful guardians to all the animals on the farm. Dewey loves everyone big and small and is Mr. Personality! Sky is shy when meeting new people. She is sweet, but nervous and takes awhile to warm up. Dewey likes sleeping by the animals and Sky likes to sleep in her kennel. We think it makes her feel safe. Swimming in the pond is one of their favorite activities, they love to wrestle, and are learning to walk on a lead. Sky and Dewey will come to you neutered/spayed, up to date on vaccines, up to date on flea/tick preventatives, and microchipped. 

Applicants must have a secure and visible 6 ft fence. In order for your application to be approved, you must also pass a home check and a vet check which includes having at least a two year vet history. Dewey and Sky can be adopted in Missouri and surrounding states: Illinois, Iowa, Kansas, Nebraska, Minnesota, and Wisconsin. We are able to transport Dewey and Sky to those states. If you would like to give Dewey and Sky their furever home, please fill out an application on our website. 

Being fostered in Ruthven, IA

animal.description:
Leonardo is a smart boy in search of a little courage. He needs a confident owner and a quiet home in order to blossom. He likes other dogs his size with goofy, playful personalities and would benefit from a furry sibling that could show him the ropes. He's a bit on the nervous side, so a home with older children and no cats to chase would be ideal. 

In the home Leo is a true gentleman - smart, assertive, and playful with a touch of couch potatoe. He knows all of his basic commands and will happily show them off to you for some treats! He loves to snuggle and be near his humans, but can play independently when left alone as well. 

Outside the home, Leo can be timid and may require a slow introduction to new people. While he enjoys other dogs, his nervousness can make him a little reactive when greeting them on leash. This reactive behavior stems from uncertainty and the feeling that he has no ability to run away when he's restricted by the leash. If he can't run away from the scary new dog approaching him - he will bark LOUDLY to get them to go away. Off leash, however, Leo is a star. He feels free to greet other dogs on his terms and is often put into group play with his trainer to help build his confidence and keep him socialized. 

At the end of the day, all Leo wants and needs is a quiet home to call his own, a patient owner to show him the ropes and a few longs walks a day to stretch his legs. In return, you will get the unconditional love of a dog that's been misunderstood for most of his life. A dog that just wants someone to finally call his own. If you think this may be you, please contact us for a private meet and greet with our Leo! 

 

Follow us on Facebook for additional updates and sneak peeks of new dogs! https://www.facebook.com/reachrescue

If approved, there is a $20 adoption fee for cats, and kittens. Adult dogs adoption fee is $75.00. Adoption fees for adult dogs at the shelter more than 2 weeks reduces to $25. Adoption fee for puppies or purebred dogs (no papers) is $100.  If not spayed or neutered, a deposit is required. The deposit is $130 for dogs and $55 for cats. Your deposit is returned after the animal is spayed/neutered. All animals adopted from the shelter MUST be spayed/neutered. Dogs arriving at the shelter receive DA2PP and Bordetella. Cats receive a vaccine for Rhinotracheitis-Calici-Panleukopenia-Chlamydia Psittaci. The animals at our shelter have been picked up stray. Please remember this when requesting additional information about the animals. Questions can be emailed to emporiakansasanimalshelter@gmail.com

animal.description:
Meet Cinder a beautiful Shepherd girl who we estimate to be about 3 yrs old. She is learning to walk on a leash, but would need some additional training.  She is not recommended for families with young kids as they may knock her down.  She needs to be an only dog.

animal.description:
***PLEASE READ ENTIRE BIO BEFORE APPLYING***
Meet Miss Marilyn Monroe! Aptly named after a true diva, Marilyn is as dramatic as they come. She likes to cuddle and love on her people, but only on her terms. She loves to play, but she can be sensitive if it’s “too much”. And she plays well with dogs of all sizes, but she insists on being in charge. 

Marilyn is a smart cookie and incredibly food motivated. No matter if she's napping or playing, she's always ready to work for a treat. She would love nothing more than to find an adopter who wants to teach her a bunch of tricks.

We believe Marilyn came from an abusive situation, because she was fearful of being touched in certain places. She has nipped in the past, but after a lot of rehabbing, she is much more trusting. She will need an adopter who is patient and experienced, and understands that rehabbing an abused dog is an ongoing process. 

If you're interested in adopting this pet please fill out our matchmaking questionnaire (www.rescuefromthehart.org).  We are volunteer based and will do our best to get back to you within 72 hours.  Please do not call as our phone is intended for emergencies only. If we feel that one of our dogs is a good match we will set up a private meet and greet  We do not have a physical location where you can come and meet all the dogs at once, so meet and greets may take a little time to coordinate.  Our requested adoption donation is $350 and all adopters are required to fill out an adoption agreement.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website. All of our dogs and cats are in foster homes and we have no paid staff. If you have questions concerning a specific animal, PLEASE fill out an application and the foster parent will be in touch. We will not arrange any home visits with any of our dogs and cats until your application is processed. Please understand our foster parents are precious to our 2nd Chance family; without them we cannot function, so we do our best to not burden them with multiple appointments. Our foster parents will choose their top 3 applications and arrange home visits with these applicants. The adopter will be chosen at that time. The process can take anywhere from a week to a month. We want to make sure our little furry ones are placed in their 'forever home' and never have to go through a rehoming again!Prince is an amazing little dude. He is doing great here at the ranch with all the other dogs. He loves to play with Murphy and the two of them beat up on each other :) They would make a great pair to go together :)Prince can try to be 'bossy' with other pups so we need a family that will not allow him to do so. He LOVES people and is going to make someone a fantastic family member :) We are requiring the following in an adopter so please do not apply if you do not meet his needs1. Fenced yard2. Another pup for him to have as his forever friend.Please fill out an adoption application:
Adoption application (Dog)
Adoption Application (Cat)

Please understand we do not adopt out dogs to
families with children under the age of 5. We do not adopt dogs to renters. Some dogs will have fence requirements while others may not.

A pet is a lifetime commitment. The dogs and cats in our system find themselves there, for the most part, because their humans did not have the same loyalty to them as they did to their owners. We do not take the adoption process lightly, and will do everything in our power to make sure the animal is placed correctly the first time around for your sake and theirs. Thank you for choosing to adopt not shop!

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Over night 1/30:
Pirate is a sweetheart! He's so well behaved, loving, and an easy going dog.

While Pirate was away for his overnight, he enjoyed a walk around the block, shopping at Pet Supermarket, playing with toys, relaxing and snoozing. He appeared to 'watch tv' while we were hanging out before bed.

Pirate rides well in the car. He'd probably prefer to ride shot gun if the front seat is open. He was fine in the backseat if both front seats were occupied. He settled into the house quickly, was perfect inside, and preferred to stay close by us. He looked forward to his meals and didn't waste any time finishing his dinner and breakfast.

He was good on the leash as we walked around the block in the neighborhood. We spent some time walking around in the yard several times because he didn't want to go much further. Pirate has a playful nature. He tugged and played with a squeaky llama and then fell asleep next to it. We got him a Nerf infinity tug toy at Pet Supermarket, and he enjoyed playing tug o war. He also liked using it as a chew toy.

Pirate is super chill, doesn't bark much, and is great companion.
Dog for a day with Pie Pie 1/14:
When we first met him, he was so sweet. Seemed very open and excited to meet new people, keen for cuddles and any opportunities to play tug-of-war with his rope toy! . He was really great and calm in the car- stayed put pretty much the whole time. Inside our home, he was also very respectful. He is a good listener and responds to any 'No' and other basic commands really well. He was quite funny with his little tug-of-war rope toy and regularly brought it to us or dropped it at our feet as a signal for playtime. Also loves just chilling out and being pet/cuddled. On walks, he was great on the leash. Rarely pulls, and if you give a little tug to change direction, he will easily follow your lead. Otherwise, he usually walks right beside you. Lastly, we took him to an open field park and were able to let his leash go to play fetch with his rope toy, which he really loved. And even off-leash he listened very well and always came back to us after fetching his toy. Overall, a very great day with a sweet and fun dog.
PER OUR VET AT THIS TIME PIRATE WOULD BENEFIT BY EATING ZD DRY FOOD. ZD IS GOOD FOR THE SKIN AND ALLERGIES.

Pirate is an Old English Bulldog but our system doesn't carry his breed. Pirate is a super sweet, loveable dog. Tug a war is his favorite game and just like any other bulldog, he loves food. Now Pirate has to be food that won't affect his skin. Even though he is big he wants to be a lap dog if given the chance.
Pirates little companion Molly got adopted leaving Pirate at the rescue alone. Pirate did have some medical concerns that have all been taken care of. Now it is his turn to go home. It is recommended that he be the only pet. He is a very easy dog despite his size. He will go outside do his business and then be happy to watch tv with you. Regretfully, Pirate's owner was not able to care for him any longer. Pirate is good with all children and people. He is a very loving dog.
Pirate does not particularly care for other dogs and is fine being only pet. Pirate is easily startled when he's asleep, and owners suggested not just walking up to him, but to talk to him/call his name as you approach him. He is almost 8 yrs after all, and is entitled to some senior quirks~Pirate, like many dogs, will go and hide if there is heavy rain or a thunder storm. Pirate is a wonderful dog for an adult home where he can share their loving personalities and have safe place to spend his golden years:)

animal.description:
Boris is a male mixed breed dog, who came to our shelter as a stray in October. He is being overlooked, perhaps because he has a poor kennel presence. He is like a teenage boy who needs direction on how best to channel his happy energy. Boris loves to play in the yard with toys, he’s pretty good on a leash, is food motivated, so easy to train. He already knows sit, and Paw.
Boris is a good dog that has tolerated such a stressful shelter environment for several months, which is testament to his stellar personality. Boris recently got to go on an adventure with a volunteer. She reports that Boris was great in the car and really enjoyed sticking his nose out the window to smell 'all the things'. She took him for walks in City Park, Armstrong Park and Uptown and he was a gentlemen with people he met and when he saw another dog he was curious but not overbearing.
Not surprisingly, Boris is more relaxed outside of the shelter environment and wanted to be pet and loved on. Boris is waiting for his forever home. Is it you? 
Boris is a 2 year old black mouth cur mix (we think)....
he’s neutered, 59 lbs, up to date on shots, and ready to play! His adoption fee is $67 and he is at the Jefferson Parish Animal Shelter in Louisiana. Boris loves to play with stuffy toys and rope toys. He really likes to play tug o war!! Boris isn’t a “Hugger” and is a little aloof. We don’t know if it’s because he’s a bit on edge at the shelter, or if in general he’s aloof. He will let you pet him, but he’s not needy. He does love a good game of “keep a way” and takes immense joy having you try to “get the toy” from him. Boris knows “sit”, “stay”, and “paw”. He tested well with another dog at the shelter but a meet and greet is recommended as Boris  can be a 'humper'. . Boris is heartworm negative, yay! To meet Boris email ryeaton@jeffparish.net or call 504 736-6111 to make an appointment!

Adoption fee includes vaccinations, spay/neuter, heartworm test, and microchip.

Call 504 736-6111 to meet Boris!
*Dogs are pending behavior and other-animal assessment unless otherwise noted here.


Available for adoption, foster, or rescue at:

Jefferson Parish Animal Shelter 1 Humane Way, Harahan, LA 70123
504 736-6111
Please provide ID number when visiting shelter. Thanks!

animal.description:
Hey human, my name is River. I’m a 9-year-old, 67 lb. Golden Retriever and I’m so glad to be with TGRR! Can you believe that for the first 9 years of my life I didn’t know what a toy was? Yeah, I didn’t live like most “household pets” live, because well…. I wasn’t a “household pet,” but we don’t need to rehash old details. Let me ask you this:  are you looking for your first dog ever? If so, then we wouldn’t be a good fit. You see, I’m not a perfect dog, but here’s a friendly reminder:  no dog is perfect, especially not us rescues. But rescue pooches are the best pooches because you get to see us blossom! So yeah, I’m a work in progress, but deep down, I’m a really sweet guy ? I’m learning so many new things since coming to TGRR. I’m learning that I don’t have to bark at new people, how to walk on a leash, and they’re teaching me how to ‘sit’ and ‘stay’ and other things like that. Here’s the good news:  I am a really smart dog, and once I get to know you, we’ll be BFFs forever! I’d love to live in a quiet place, with no kids in the house and no cats, and I’d really like to be an only dog and have you all to myself!  In other words, if you will rescue me, then I’ll rescue you.

**Our adoption applications are not open, if interested in River please fill out a CONTACT FORM ON TGRR.ORG!

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
Name: Chong

DOB: 7/2/2019

Adoption Fee: 375.00

Hi friends! My name is Iggy and I'm super excited to meet you. I've been living in Minneapolis for the last eight months. I came from a tough situation in Texas where I was called Chong, but Iggy is my preferred name. I weigh 50 pounds (all muscle!) and recently celebrated my first birthday! Woohoo!

My breed is Blue Heeler (Australian Cattle Dog) and Bully mix with a little bit of German Sheperd. I am a high energy dog and I have a big silly wiggly happy personality. I make my mom laugh every day. I love playing hard with the other dog in my house. I also try to play with the cat. Sometimes he plays with me but sometimes he swats at me. I can't figure him out! I would do best in a house with a playful tolerant dog or dogs that can help keep me busy. I would do okay in a home with no other pets if there are people at home most of the time who can give me lots of walks and attention. Also I am not into dog parks. Too many dogs at once stresses me out! But I love playing one-to-one or in small groups in my yard.

I am looking to join an active home where we will go on daily walks (or runs or hikes!) I can go and go. Also, I do great walking on a leash when it is attached to my harness. Although sometimes I'll pull when I see a squirrel!

In addition to daily exercise, I need a home where I can get a lot of human attention. Otherwise, I get bored. And when I'm bored, I let you know by barking and bringing you my toys. You can keep me entertained with puzzle toys, tug toys, fetch, chews, brain games, training games, or a frozen peanut butter filled Kong is great! Did I mention I completed basic training? I'm a good listener and eager to please. An advanced training class would be something fun we could do to bond together!

At the end of the day, I love to cuddle up with you. Best of all is my head on your lap. I'd love to sleep in bed with you too. I am great snuggler and I give very gentle kisses.

A couple things you should know about me: I should only live with adults or older kids who know how to be calm. Sometimes I bark at new people until I am sure they are my friend. I mean no harm! Sometimes I jump up on people but only because I want to give my new friend some affection. If you remind me, I do a pretty good job of sitting & staying, especially if you have some treats in your pocket when new people come over!

I hope you will take chance on a great guy like me. We are going to have so much fun together!

An adoption application is the best way to show your interest in an animal.

Please check out our website, www.ruffstartrescue.org for more details and additional pictures on any of our animals!

All Ruff Start dogs and cats are spayed/neutered, up to date on age appropriate vaccines, microchipped, dewormed, and on monthly flea/tick and heartworm prevention (dogs) as well as heartworm tested (dogs).

Ruff Start Rescue is a foster based rescue. Animals are located in homes throughout Minnesota. We do not have a facility where animals are kept.

Ruff Start Rescue Adoption Policies: http://www.ruffstartrescue.org/info/display?PageID=11744

animal.description:
Echo is a wonderful girl with tons of love to give! Echo is deaf and because of this, she will need an owner who will be willing to use training methods that will fit her needs such as teaching her hand signals. Because she cannot hear, sometimes when she gets excited she makes a lot of silly noises. She is kennel trained and keeps her run at the boarding facility very clean. She loves to burrow under her blankets. She also loves to play with stuffed animals and rope toys. Echo is not dog aggressive, but she is very fearful when meeting new dogs. She would be best either as an only pet or in a home with a very mellow dog friend. Also because she can be fearful of dogs, she will most likely need multiple intros with any potential doggy friends.

Echo is an incredibly smart dog and learns quickly. She has the cutest wiggle dance ever when she is happy to see her humans. Echo has a lot of energy and will thrive with someone who will give her plenty of daily exercise. Echo needs a home without cats. She is GREAT with kids.  She is very affectionate and can sometimes be a little overexcited and may knock over a small toddler. This is something can be worked on but older kids may be better suited for her energy level.

After a rough start of mistreatment and abandonment by his prior owners, Moose simply wants to feel safe and learn to trust. This boy is house trained, leash trained, crate trained and knows sit, lay down and no. He is also working on bell training for his potty needs! Moose is trustworthy with free roam but does have separation anxiety when left for long periods of time. He will bark to alert, but knows not to dig or chew. His favorite hobbies include chasing a ball, playing with squeaky toys or enjoying a treat filled Kong. Moose does well with other dogs, cats and kiddos are unknown at this time but at this point we suggest older only. This handsome young boy will thrive in a positive environment with proper boundaries and love and affection. Could you be the new family Moose so desires?

Giant Breed Experienced Homes Only.
To see the most up to date adoption status of this dog, please visit www.bigdogshugepaws.com
This is just one of hundreds of gentle giants available for adoption at BDHPI! It is best not to get your heart set on any one particular dog upfront because there is no guarantee they will still be available once you are approved or that they are even the right match for your family. Purebred puppies are only eligible for adoption to giant breed experienced homes.

8.  Dog to Dog Food Issues – N/A

When brought near cats, he was hesitant to approach them and when they hissed at him, he ran in the other direction. Still, slow and steady introductions are always recommended when bringing any new animals home.

animal.description:
**Teddy is being Fostered in the St Louis area.**

Teddy might be the cutest pup in town, and he wants his forever family to know these 10 things about him!

1.	I am a Rotti-Mastiff mix, and I am about 4-5 years old.  

2.	I tip the scales at about 110lbs, and that is a healthy weight for me.
 
3.	I really love people.  I think I would do well in a home with kids older than 14.

4.	The words that best describe me are adorable, sweet, friendly, and affectionate. 

5.	Although I’ve mostly only met larger dogs, so far I haven’t found a canine that I didn’t get along with.  As long as my new owners were willing to give me a proper introduction to their dogs, I think I could happily live in a home with other pups.   

6.	I’m very interested in the resident feline in my foster home.  I am learning to be redirected but the jury is still out if I can be trusted to cohabitate with cats.  

7.	My two favorite things are getting attention from humans and playing with toys (I’ve been known to carry a ball or bone around with me on my walks!).  

8.	I am housebroken, wonderful in the crate, and I am perfecting my leash skills!
 
9.	I have osteoarthritis in my both my back and front legs.  It doesn’t bother me too much but I will probably need to take medication and/or supplements for the rest of my life.  While I can and do go up/down a small flight of stairs at my Foster Home, a home with no more than a short flight of stairs would be best.  Luckily for everyone, I take medicine and treats very gently.

10.	I am fully vaccinated, heartworm negative, neutered, and microchipped. 

Ready to give Teddy the forever home of his dreams?  Fill out our Adoption Application, located at www.bullpenrescue.org under the 'work with us' tab.

We highly recommend that our potential adopters fill out an online application as soon as possible, as it greatly expedites the process of finding the right dog for your situation.  

Our dogs are available for adoption nationwide but preference is given to adopters willing to do an in-person meeting.  Please understand that our dogs are not adopted on a first-come, first-serve basis, but rather we strive for a "perfect placement" so we know that they will not be failed again.

animal.description:
BUNNY is a beautiful, happy-go-lucky,  9 month old terrier-pit mix.   She loves to play outside, run around in the yard and play in her kiddie pool.   She loves peanut butter, sticks, and all types of chew toy.  Bunny doesn't realize she weighs almost 50 pounds and thinks she is still a lap dog!       She loves any type of chew toy, cuddling her humans, and will even enjoy a bath if she can enjoy licky pads with peanut butter!   She is smart, and goofy, and 100% puppy.  Bunny is still an energetic puppy and will make an amazing addition to any family. 

All our adoption fees include spay/neuter, micro-chip, up-to-date vaccinations, including rabies thru date of adoption. This pup tested heartworm negative, and is on regular monthly heartworm prevention & on flea/tick prevention. 

In order to be considered for one of our beautiful pups, please go to our website and complete and application: https://www.mustluvdogs.org/adoptable-pets.
Please note that we are a DUE DILIGENCE adoption organization. Part of our approval process requires, among other things:
* Experienced pet home with verifiable vet references/history preferred, but we realize that everyone has to start somewhere, so all applications will be considered.
*The majority, but not all, of our pets require a fenced yard or secure enclosure.  In the case of apartments, we require Landlord approval and designated dog area in complex.
*Verifiable good veterinary history INCLUDING regular vaccination/visits and good Heartworm Prevention history is a MUST!
*Adopter must be able to have time to spend with the pup and be able to provide the pup a safe environment to live.
*ALL our dogs are expected to be primarily INSIDE dogs.  They MUST sleep inside the home.  We truly understand that some folks have working dogs (i.e. farmers, ranchers,etc); however, the majority of our dogs have had a rough life prior to coming to us & we want to make sure that they are showered with LUV & maybe even a bit spoiled for the rest of their lives. 

Other facts are also considered, including whether children or other pets are a good fit with the dog. 

Must Luv Dogs reserves the right to deny any applications that we don't think are a good fit with the pup. Our first & foremost concern is the dog's best interest. It is our MISSION to place them in a home that is a great fit for their needs for a lifetime of luv & being part of a family.
*We will consider adoptions in any area; however, will do not ship or transport puppies under the age of 12 mos. We will ONLY transport an adult dog on a transport approved by MLD, at adopter's expense.
* In order to be affordable and afford every family an opportunity to have a pup of their own, we keep our Adoption Fees low; however, please keep in mind that the fees we charge do not cover all costs for the pup.  Any additional donations are greatly appreciated!

Please note that all of our pets are in private foster homes. In order to reduce any stress or confusion for our pups, we require a completed, approved application BEFORE setting up a meet & greet for any of our pups.  Alternatively, you are always welcome to come meet any of our pups at one of our regular Adoption Events.   Our events are always posted on PetFinder OR on our Facebook page: https://www.facebook.com/mustLUVdogs.org.

Finally, THANK YOU for considering Must Luv Dogs for your next pet. 

*Most dogs require a fenced area in yard. 
*Apartments okay IF nearby dog park or walking trails (with landlord appoval).
*ALL dogs must be INSIDE dogs and treated a part of family. 
*We are a DUE DILIGENCE Adoption Rescue.  
*Must have good Vet history & Heartworm prevention is a MUST!
*ALL dogs are fully vetted, spay/neutered and microchipped prior to adoption.

FYI:   Even though this pup tested heartworm negative, we provide the following procedural information for your information:  Any of our pups who test HW+ are treated with the *slow kill method of treatment.   The *slow-kill method, simply stated, is a 30 day regiment of  doxycycline followed by a monthly dose of Advantage Multi for 12 months, then retesting.   Most dogs test negative after one year of following this treatment; however, we always recommend that potential adopters consult & follow the advice of their family veterinarian upon adopting any of our hw+ pups.   Although the fast-kill method is still considered the "gold-standard" by the AVA, and may be preferred by some vets; the slow-kill method has proven to be effective in our rescue. The main reason we utilize this method is due to our limited financial constraints and the high number of our rescue pups that are infected.   In the cases of severe infection and if the pup is highly symptomatic, we sometimes use the fast-kill approach instead.   Again, we recommend for you to consult with your veterinarian after the adoption is complete and follow their recommendations.

animal.description:
Buddy is a sweet senior boy. He takes some time to warm up to you and show you who he really is. He's laid back, sweet, and pretty lazy. Not a bad thing at all.

He deserves a home where he can nap most of the day and come to you for some serious loving when he wants it.He prefers soft blankets and plush beds so he can fluff them to his liking.

He is a little hard of hearing, and maybe his sight too. And he has hip dysplasia. But that really doesn't change much. He loves when his foster mom sings to him and dances around the house. It makes him feel like a spring chicken! He loves it.

We are here for a lifetime of support for this boy.He just needs someone who can look past his imperfections and give him a soft landing.

Adopt Buddy and find your new best friend. He has wisdom and lots of love for the right people. Apply at doghouserescueacademy.org

animal.description:
Jethro is the biggest sweetheart when it comes to the people he knows. He is a 70# bundle of medium-high energy who thinks he's a lap dog and loves to cuddle. Jethro LOVES balls. He has been house-trained and is good with recall (come), sit, down, heel, place (to his bed), and a few other commands. He is also a decent running/walking partner, but does need to learn to be around other dogs while on a leash better. Jethro has shown some resource guarding behaviors with treats and his home territory, and therefore, we think it is best he go to a home without children and reduced traffic in and out of the home. Jethro does well with people and other dogs after he has met them and is comfortable with them, but can be unfriendly with people/dogs he doesn't know. For this reason, dog parks would not be a good option for him and an invisible fence has not worked well for him in the past. He is good with cats, but will chase and try to play with them. 
You can also watch for stories, pictures and video's about me on our Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/groups/40103261297/
 
Adoption fee: $375
 
Adoption fees for all dogs/puppies include a $50 refundable training deposit. Complete your basic training program and provide a copy of the certificate within 4 months (120 days) of adoption and we will refund $50 of the original adoption fee.
 
All dogs/puppies have been fully vetted including spay/neuter, micro-chipping, worming, heartworm testing and preventative treatment, flea/tick preventative, and all required age appropriate vaccinations. As required by Wisconsin Act 90, all dogs will have received a veterinarian exam (CVI) within the past 30 days.
 
Our adoption process requires the submission of an application. Applications and Adoption Rules can be found on our website, on the "HOW TO ADOPT" tab. Upon receipt of the completed application, we will process the application including: contact with your veterinarian and completion of a home visit. Please be sure to include the contact information for your vet as we will call. If your vet requires an information release, please be sure to contact them as soon as you submit your application. We are a group of volunteers with families and jobs, so please be patient and allow a few days for our response.
 
JR's Pups-N-Stuff Dog Sellers License 270089-DS

animal.description: You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.All of the animals posted on our site have been temperament tested. While not all are in the immediate area, once we have processed and approved your application, we will move the dog to our adoptive area for you to meet, greet and hopefully adopt. Sometimes we will have more than one application on a dog. That does not mean it automatically goes to another family but you should be aware of the fact that until you are approved and set up for the meet/greet.. the dog could get adopted by another applicant.NOTE - TUCKER IS LISTED AS A COURTESY FOR AUGUSTA DOG ADOPTIONS IN STAUNTON, VIRGINIA. POTENTIAL ADOPTERS MUST TRAVEL TO STAUNTON FOR THE MEETING.For more information and to apply to adopt, please visit www.augustadogadoptions.orgTucker is a 10-11 year old pit mix who weighs about 60 pounds. Poor Tucker has just never been able to find a family who loves him unconditionally and can make a commitment to him!Tucker is a very laid back guy who enjoys lounging in the sun, napping and watching TV. He is also happy to go for runs or chase balls around the yard. Tucker does not care for other animals and does take his possessions at little too seriously at times. He would be successful in a quiet, adult only home where he can play when he wants to play and relax when he wants to relax. He is house trained and has very good house manners.A reduced adoption fee of $100 does apply for Tucker, our seniors, special medical and behavioral needs dogs and other 'slow to adopt' dogs!Augusta Dog Adoptions is an all- volunteer, foster- based rescue. We take applications online and are scheduling individual adoptions in the Waynesboro, VA area during the pandemic. A $175.00 adoption fee ($300 for puppies under 6 months old) helps us take care of all the dogs we rescue. All dogs are spayed/neutered, tested for heartworm and tick borne diseases (if old enough), microchipped, and vaccinated for rabies (if old enough), distemper/parvo and bordetella. They are also treated for internal and external parasites. Many dogs also receive extensive medical care such as dental work and major surgeries. For more information and to apply to adopt, please visit www.augustadogadoptions.org

animal.description:
Meet Zyan! He is about 1.5 years old and 117 pounds. Our Giant lovebug Cane Corso Zyan is still battling for his health and happiness. Brought to PCAS several months ago, as an owner requested euthanasia because they chose not to give him the medical attention he desperately needed, Zyan was a BIG BOY with BIG BILLS and we stepped in to help him. Since then, he has seen multiple specialists who all agreed surgery wasn't the path to take. They also agreed Zyan could live a long, happy life if given the continued care he needed. So instead of surgery, Zyan has been undergoing treadmill hydrotherapy 3 times a week and physical therapy in addition to that. All of this is in an effort to help his stability, improve his mobilization, and avoid total hip replacement on this very young dog. There is no guarantee this won't be the only option in the future... but the 8-12 weeks of combination therapy is his best shot at a quality of life he deserves. This is a significant undertaking of both FUND$ and TIME and we are beyond grateful to his foster family for committing to Zyan's medical rehabilitation so completely (driving him to and from appts, helping him at home, etc). yan is also on the hunt for his forever home and can be moved there if there is an angel on earth looking to take on our big boy.

Donations to Zyan's care or care can be made via PayPal.me/maxxandme; Venmo @maxxandmepetrescue; checks mailed to 12157 W Linebaugh Ave #181 Tampa, Fl 33626

Z He is wonderful with his young foster kids but Leary of new children. He LOVES toys and squeakers and tug o'war and prancing around the house playing with them all by himself. His bark is imposing and intimidating but it belies the giant goofball he really is. He LIVES to snuggle and is loving all the books he's reading and screen time he's getting with his foster kids when they settle in the evenings. He's potty trained and well-mannered. He doesn't counter surf, is non destructive, wants a yard to enjoy and a family of his own to continue to grow with and learn from. He's being fostered as an only and is fine with that but was also in senior play groups when he was in boarding and did great with other dogs. Is yours the family to bring Zyan across the finish line of his journey? He deserves a champion and he's ready to have that now.

Zyan is neutered, up to date on vaccines, and microchipped. Adoption donation is $250.
If you would like to meet any of our dogs, please fill out an adoption application on www.maxxandme.org
Maxx & Me is an all volunteer, all foster home rescue and do not have a shelter. Please allow at least 48 hours for applications to be processed (missing information may slow the process, so please take your time and be thoughtful in your answers). All dogs posted are available (so no need to ask). We place dogs based on best home for each dog and not order of applications received. Email us at maxxandmerescue@gmail.com for updates and questions. Thank you for choosing rescue.

I would do best in a home where I will get daily exercise, not too much alone time, and some continued training and socialization.  I love my people so much, I hate to be away from them, can you blame me? 
 I can get really excited  especially on a leash and this leads me to barking and pulling towards dogs, especially on leash but I am working on my manners when this happens so I will need someone who will be patient with me while I learn what to do instead! 
I would like a home without another dog at this time but I do enjoy going to play with dogs outside of my house! 
A house with a yard would be a bonus too! Do I sound like the perfect buddy for you?!?

Due to the current events, the rescue is not able to host adoption events.  Please fill out an application and we will conduct phone interviews and set up outdoor meet and greets! www.thegooddogrescue.org

Shida is a sweet, 9yo, 95lb Alaskan Malamute mix who is ready to find her forever home. She came to our rescue as an owner surrender when they became disabled and were no longer able to care for her. 

Shida had some health issues and was overweight when she cam e to us. She has since lost over 50lbs and gotten her health issues under control. She also recently had a dental and is all set with her clean teefies!

Shida loves people and enjoys walks, and lounging outside or on her bed. Shida does resource guard her treat/food/toys so will need a family experienced with that behavior. Shida can do well with dogs but no overly excited, hyper or dominant dogs. And she will need to be watched as she will get snappy with other dogs when it comes to her toys, food, ect. 

Kids over 12 and no apartments, condo, or townhouses.  She's loud when she wants your attention.

Large dog breed experience required.  There are maintenance issues for large breeds that owner should be aware of.

Shida is UTD on shots, microchipped and spayed. Her adoption fee is $400.

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

Hi - I'm Mischa! I'm a fun loving, high energy girl! I love running, eating and wrestling with my foster siblings!

I love toys too (unfortunately the "stuffed" ones don't last long around me :)

I used to be chained up lot before I was rescued - so I need a home that has a big fenced yard where I can run! Squirrels and bunnies entice me and I love to chase them, I just can't help myself.

Initially I was nervous about everything and now I'm getting the hang of this being a well loved pet. My foster dad is taking me to doggie stores and I'm meeting new people. These people are giving me treats so I LET them pet me . Sorta a WIN/WIN!

I think I'll be an amazing family dog for someone but you might need to be patient and let me fall madly in love with you on my terms (might be 2 days or 2 weeks). AND, I really could use a companion animal to remind me how to "dog" as I'm still working on the play thing.

If you think we would be a good match, please submit an application.

~Looking forward to meeting you

Date of birth (estimated):
9/25/19

Good with Dogs: Yes (with proper introductions - no small dogs)

Good with Cats: No

House Trained: Yes

Adoption Fee:

$300

If you are interested in meeting or adopting this animal, please read the following before submitting an adoption application on our website - fureverhomerescue.com.

Adoption fee includes spay/neuter, microchip, age appropriate vaccinations, 4Dx test (covers tick-borne diseases (Anaplasmosis , Lymes, Ehrlichiosis) as well as heart worm) & de-worming. We ask that our dogs live indoors unless otherwise stated & agreed upon. Applicants must live in MN within a reasonable distance from the Twin Cities Metro Area. We do not adopt out of state.

Do you believe in magic?  I just put a spell on you!  My name is Salem and I have cast a love spell over you!  Now you may suddenly find the urge to fill out my adoption application...you should definitely go ahead and do that.  I am a 2 year old, 55lb., lady, pitbull mix munchkin of sweetness!  I am house trained, crate trained, and great on a leash!  I am very smart and I am working on learning some commands.  I am a super duper sweet, laid back sugarplum.  Not to brag, but I can play some pretty awesome games of fetch.  I am looking for a home where I would be the only animal.  I also do well with older children.  I am not fond of felines so please none of those in my forever home.  I would be happy living with you in a house or apartment!  I am currently battling heart worm, but as soon as I am all good (probably about February), we can start living our best lives together!  Fill out that application and the rest of our lives will be full of magic!


My adoption fee is $150 and includes my spay/neuter, vaccinations, wellness exam, heartworm test, and microchip! If you're interested in meeting/adopting me, please visit www.rescueonespringfield.com/our-adoption-process/adoption-application/ and fill out the form! We do adopt out of state with vet references and video home check. *Adopter is responsible for coming to get the dog and returning the dog if the adoption does not work out* 

Don't forget to LIKE us on Facebook!-www.facebook.com/rescueonespringfield

*Remember, dogs are pack animals. Because of this, Rescue One does not adopt to outdoor-only homes. Pets are family and are not disposable.  Please make sure that you are 100% committed to a pet before considering adding one to your home.

animal.description:
Meet Ollie. He is a Gulf Coast Treasure and the quintessential Lab that you can count on. He is loyal, smart, dog-friendly, and a great companion. And, like most labs, he is food-driven and enjoys treats after every retrieve. At 5 years old and 176 pounds, he needs to lose around 75 lbs. Who can't stand to lose a few COVID pounds? You can navigate that goal together. So gear up and get out there, he will be with you every step of the way sharing experiences that become your legacy.

Disclaimer: Please know this is a recently rescued dog that is still transitioning into a new home environment. Training, and even personality and energy levels are constantly evolving as the dog starts to feel better emotionally and physically. Your new dog will take days or even weeks to fully settle into his or her true self. What you read in this bio is a snapshot of this dog’s evolving personality. Additionally, the age listed is an estimate provided by the shelter and/or veterinarian. Different vets can provide different age estimates. So always consider the lab you are adopting to be within an age range of a couple of years of what is listed. Also remember, while we are a lab rescue, we do not have papers on these dogs, we cannot confirm any breed specific claims, and many of these dogs may be mixed with other breeds.

IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN ADOPTING ONE OF OUR DOGS... please visit us at www.luslabs.org and fill out an adoption application.  Once submitted, one of our Adoption Coordinators will be in touch!

animal.description:
Duffy is a one year old boy looking for his forever home. He was found stray in Louisiana and brought to a nearby shelter. He was absolutely terrified and it was clear that people hadn’t been kind to him in the past. With some TLC at the shelter from wonderful volunteers showing him love, Duffy was able to move on to a Paws4Rescue foster family. They were very patient and kind with him and allowed him to come out of his shell little by little until he gained confidence and could enjoy being with the other dogs in his foster home.
At first, he was afraid of most everything. “I think of him as a budding rose,” his foster mom says. “When he first came to us, he wouldn’t even make eye contact, but now he has blossomed into a beautiful, comical dog! He occasionally needs some encouragement when something catches his eye he’s unfamiliar with, but he even walks well on leash with us now. He enjoys riding in the car and running errands with us. He’s not very treat motivated, but he loves cheese! We will miss him lots, but we look forward to him finding his forever family.”
Duffy weighs about 40 pounds. He is housebroken, crate trained, neutered, microchipped, and up to date on vaccines. If you’d like to adopt Duffy, please go to Paws4Rescue.org and send us your application.
