animal.description:
Jazy was a stray roaming the streets of NYC in August and brought to the NYC Animal Care Centers.  She wasn't in good shape.  She had pyoderma and some behavioral issues such as anxiety and fear.  She was then listed for euthanasia due to overcrowding at the shelter,  Pound Hounds was able to save his life due to a foster stepping up.


JAZZY'S STATS:

Approx 3 years old

47 lbs

Crate-Trained:  Does NOT like the crate but fine alone in the house.

Good with dogs with proper introductions. 

Kids over 16, please

UTD on vaccinations, spayed and microchipped.  

Good with Strangers: Needs to take the time to sniff and bark. Easy to get to know women but has a tougher time around strange/new men.       

On Leash: As she gets to know you, she will tug on the leash quite a bit. It ends up being her favorite toy to play with. But, as she has gotten used to the neighborhood, that behavior has lessened tremendously. Continuing with treats, training, having her on a harness, and sticking to a schedule will continue to lessen the behavior. 

Housetrained:  Once Jazzy is on a set schedule, she does not go in the house. She has to trust that you will be taking her out. Before that trust is there, she gets a bit confused and may have a few accidents.             

Here is what his foster mom has to say:

Jazzy needs a really energetic home that can keep up with her. Also a lot of patience!! Don’t give up on this loving girl. When you are her person, and she trusts you, all she wants to do is cuddle and be with you. She also needs a strong leader who will be strict with her training. Remind her not to jump on people, etc. 


THINGS I KNOW ABOUT JAZZY:

She sighs a lot, especially when she’s trying to sleep and YOU’RE still awake. It is actually really funny, she will always let you know when you are bothering her. She has such a big personality. 

She will drink out of the toilet!! Make sure she has water when she needs it (she will pee a lot if you don’t watch her water intake) but just keep the bathroom closed if you are worried about this.

Her medication (flea, tick, heartworm) is due on the 3rd of every month!
	
She is the type of dog that stares into your eyes, with love 
	
Her tail will still wag even when she is barking at someone. She is always trying to see if she trusts someone…. 
	
She just wants to play with other dogs, gets really excited especially while on the leash

Squirrels and rabbits are her things! She will really really try to chase after them, always keep an eye out.

She was a stray, she’s used to the rain and she will get into the garbage if you let her. It’s what she is used to. 
	
She really enjoys ice cubes. You can randomly give them to her throughout the day and she will play with them.
	
She does not let you cut her nails. This can be a huge thing for her because she can get stressed out when it comes to her paws. Cutting her nails is a no but we have gotten her more used to wiping her paws when she comes into the house. 

My time with Jazzy has been everything that I thought having a foster dog would be! In the beginning, she is earning your trust and figuring out who her people are. Once she is more and more comfortable, she really makes the house her own. Jazzy would sleep all day if you let her but then that means she will have the zoomies all night!!! Because of this, she needs a bit more of an energetic household that will help her explore and learn more about being a dog. Jazzy can be stubborn, because of this, she needs a leader who will continue her training and be consistent and PATIENT! This is a dog who deserves all of the love and cuddles on this planet but she also deserves someone who will put the work into her to train her and keep her in your focus. Right now, Jazzy is in a female-only household with no other pets. She could really thrive with another dog who can help get her energy out but she is also really great just with her people! She is a very versatile dog. If you want a dog with a big personality, she is definitely the one for you. Jazzy hasn’t had a lot of time around men, she can get very protective and will bark but has never given us the impression that she would ever bite. She just doesn’t trust them yet, this is where a lot of positive reinforcement and treats will come into play. She needs consistency. If you are at all interested and have questions, please feel free to reach out!! 


The best home for Jazzy would be out of the city, in a quiet setting.  A quiet home with not too many people coming in and out.

The only complaint a person would have walking me in a busy area, is that I will stop to say hi to every dog and child, and person I see.

I love to play with my foster siblings! My foster home consists of two little guys smaller than me and a large female who has a few pounds on me. Don’t let all this playing talk scare you though-I’m also down to cuddle on the couch and binge Netflix with my foster parents. I’m like Velcro and am never far from my humans. If you want a social dog that is also down for a calm night in, submit your app today!

In order to qualify for ALIVE Rescue Memphis's program all of the following steps must be met:

 •You must be at least 21 years of age and be able to provide ALIVE with proof of age.

 •Any current pets must be up to date on vaccinations, and be spayed/neutered. Exceptions to this will only be considered if proof of a medical explanation is provided.

 •If you currently rent, you must provide a landlord’s phone number and a copy of your executed lease.

 •All members of the family living in the home where the animal will be placed must be interviewed.

 •Applicant must live within 50 miles of Memphis if interested in adopting and within 30 miles of Memphis if interested in fostering. 

 •Allow an ALIVE Rescue Memphis representative into your home for a visit to insure that your home is safe for the potential new pet.  

  •You must allow an ALIVE Rescue Memphis representative into your home for a visit to ensure that your home is safe for the potential new pet. 

  •You must be able and willing to spend the time and money necessary to provide training, medical treatment, and proper care for a pet.

  •Currently, adoptions fees in Memphis are $275 for a dog over 4 months of age, $300 for a dog under 4 months of age. 

  •We require an additional $75 training deposit at the time of adoption. You will be required to enroll and complete a training class with your new companion at one of our approved training facilities. Once ALIVE Rescue Memphis receives proof of the completed class, this $75 deposit will be refunded.

animal.description:
Knight is living in a foster home. Submit an application from our website and then make an appointment to meet him.

Knight is not eligible for foster and will be a straight adoption.

Age: ~7
Weight: ~50 lb
Housebroken: Working on it! Needs to be on a strict schedule. 
Crate trained: Working on it! Takes 30-45 minutes to settle. 
Dog sociability: Friendly with other dogs on walks. Prefers dogs that are on the calmer side like him.
Cat sociability: Unknown
Kids: Not a match - can guard high value items/bones
Ideal home: Knight is a chill guy looking for a chill home. He isn't the biggest fan of stairs (he's working on it!) so he'd prefer a home without a ton of them.

Knight is a sweet, confident, and well-mannered gentleman who knows what he wants out of life...food, belly rubs, food, leisurely walks, food, a quiet place to hang out/nap, and some good chews to gnaw on. And he isn't afraid to let you know when he'd like some pets or is absolutely dying of starvation! He would prefer that you introduce potential guests to him before they come into his home (hint: he can be won over with treats!). He also takes his food and chews very seriously and asks that you respect his space when he's enjoying them. Although he's usually the quiet type, he will be sure to tell you if he hears any knocks, dings, barks, or squeaks that you should know about (real or televised!). His favorite bonding activities are being brushed/petted and learning new things while being given lots of treats. He knows 'sit' and is currently working on 'stay' and 'wait'. If you're looking for a buddy to lounge around and enjoy life with, Knight's your guy!

animal.description: Constance is a gorgeous fawn colored eight month old pittie mix.  Constance is such a little fighter, and lucky for her a group of construction workers witnessed her being dumped on their rural job site, and instantly brought her to us. animal.description:
COURTESY POST: Meet Raven. She was rescued by a Good Samaritan and Paws for Life is helping her find a loving, forever family for Raven. So allow us to introduce you to this sweet girl. Raven leans into you, smiles up at you with her lolling tongue, then melts into a puddle of love on the floor for some belly rubs. She loves sitting on the couch with you, rolling around and being goofy. Her clumsy and puppy-like behavior will have you laughing out loud. She loves squeaky balls. At the age of about 2-3 years, she is full of life and full of love. Raven is a people-pleaser. She is learning to “sit” on cue, but she likes to do a cute thing where she sits then puts both paws up for you to hold hands with her, then she starts to fall backwards and you have to hold her up. It's adorable! Although shy at first, Raven will form a strong bond with her “person” and become their constant companion. Could you be the one to teach this beauty what a loving home really is? She can’t wait to hear from you! Raven is 65 lbs, and her amazing foster momma from My Sidekick Dog Training is covering all her medical care, so that she'll go home vaccinated and spayed. If you can foster or adopt, please email AshleighRose312@gmail.com or call Ash at 248-921-2145.

Apply online: www.pawsforliferescue.org

Shop at Amazon to help Paws for Life earn needed donations: http://smile.amazon.com/ch/26-2505458

NOTE ABOUT BREED LABELING: Visual breed identification of dogs  is unreliable and usually inaccurate. So, for most of our adoptable  dogs, we are only guessing at predominant breed or breed mix. We get to  know each dog as an individual and will do our best to describe each of our dogs based on personality, not by breed label.

Why is labeling a dog such a big deal? A label will stick with  a dog for the rest of its life. A label can mean discrimination, losing  its home or even death. Labels are a problem for the dogs when we, as  the local experts on animals, allow adopters, politicians and community  members to think that the label we assign can predict who that dog is or will be.

Adoption Process: Complete the application at www.pawsforliferescue.org or go to the direct link at https://form.jotform.com/81935638982170. We then arrange a location, date and time for you to meet some pets. If the meeting goes well and everyone is happy, you begin the mandatory, minimum two-week adjustment period with the pet as part of your family. You will pay the non-refundable adoption fee at the start of the two-week adjustment period. This pending period allows your new dog or cat time to adjust to their new home, new people, new routine, etc., and for you to decide if it's a match and the right pet for you. At the end of two weeks (some people extend the adjustment time as needed and that's fine too), if everyone is happy, then we finalize the adoption. Feel free to email if you have any questions.

animal.description:
If you are interested in adopting me please go to www.fureverunitedrescue.com to fill out an application. 

I am in a foster home in South Texas, and will be transported to the Pacific Northwest once adopted. 

Blondie is a 7 year old gal that came to us after living much of her life on a chain. She used to be shy and unsure about her surroundings. In her foster home she has really blossomed into a social butterfly. We love to watch her zoom zoom around the yard and roll in the grass. 

Blondie is housebroken, crate trained and walks well on a leash. She is good with children and other big dogs.

TOTAL FEES FOR ADOPTION:   Adoption Fee of $275 + Texas Sales tax of 8.25%  + $150 transport fee for a total due of $447.69. The adoption fee includes all age appropriate vaccinations (spay/neuter, microchip, health certificate) and the transport fee covers transport to the Pacific Northwest on the next available date).

TRANSPORT: Currently we have monthly transports. It will be up to the adoptive family to meet the transport to pick up your new family member. Please be advised that our dogs are adopted to their forever families prior to being transported to the Pacific Northwest. Unfortunately at this time, we cannot bring dogs for a typical meet and greet situation, due to the extensiveness of the transport distance and it being unfair for the dogs who are not adopted to have to make the trip back. 

Due to the number of requests that we receive on our puppies and dogs, please be advised that all adoption applications are processed in the order received. Once we send you an application, your place in line does not get reserved until your application is returned to us.

animal.description:
Age: 2 Years
Weight: 48 lbs.
Good with dogs: Yes
Good with cats: No
Good with kids: Yes - Older
Energy Level: High
Available for Adoption: 2/6/2021 (Accepting applications Now) - Applications need to be approved before a meet and greet will be set up for any Fetching Hearts Rescue dogs.

Meet Hunter!!!  Hunter is a super sweet boy!!! He was brought to the shelter by his owner who was unable to provide him the proper exercise and socialization Hunter needed.  He has been the perfect boy since he was left by his owner.  He really loves attention!!!  He will make an amazing family dog. 

Hunter would do best with an active family or couple.  After a long day of playing in the 
fenced back yard with you or taking a long hike to explore the world, he would love to snuggle up with you.  Hunter loves toys and loves to play fetch with his people.  He is always greeting people with a wiggle wagging tail.  Look at that smile!! Hunter is waiting patiently for his forever home. 

If you want are looking for a fun, energetic and loving family member, Hunter is your guy!!!

If you would like more information on Hunter, please contact
INFO.FETCHINGHEARTS@GMAIL.COM OR COPY LINK BELOW TO APPLY AND FILL OUT AN APPLICATION: https://www.fetchingheartsrescue.org/adoption-form-online to fill out an application.

Unless otherwise indicated, all dogs adopted through Fetching Hearts have received the following before being available for adoption:

Thorough veterinary examination

All routine annual vaccinations, including Rabies, DHLPP, Bordatella (Kennel Cough), Heartworm Test, Fecal Test, Deworming, Microchip, Flea and Tick Prevention and Heartworm Prevention.

Spay/Neuter
All dogs are quarantined for two weeks outside of the shelter (puppies four weeks) to ensure they don't break with disease.

VETTING NOTE: Fetching Hearts Rescue completely vets our dogs thoroughly to the best of our knowledge based on communication with our Southern Vets. If anything is brought to our attention, we treat the dog. After adopting the dog, you will be responsible for following up with all vetting going forward.

HEARTWORM NOTE: Dogs who were treated for Heartworm can test positive up to 4-6 months after last treatment. All dogs are immediately put on Heartguard/Ivermectin following the treatment to kill the Heartworm larvae. All dogs should be re-tested after 5-6 months from the last Heartworm treatment.

Thelam is 12 years and 20lbs

Thelma is 12+ years old and has been with us once before. In her time away from us she was unfortunately hit by a car and we are working with our vets to determine the best treatment for her front limb. Right now she drags it everywhere she goes and we are working on making her a sling to wear until it can be removed.

Thelma likes to the doggy door in her foster home. This allows her to access the yard for bathroom needs as she deems necessary. She tries to keep a clean den and likes going out for walks. She has a ton of energy and fits an older Jack Russell Terrier mix to a T as she can sometimes have a little attitude. As you can see she also enjoys rolling around and being upside down. Does well with cats and other dogs.

Inquiries: adoptions@plannedpethoodrockymount.com
Adoption Application Link: https://www.plannedpethoodrockymount.com/adoptions

Click here to view our general adoption fees. Our adoption fees help to provide a portion of the care that we provide our animals.

Prior to adoption, all of our animals are altered, vaccinated, microchipped, tested for heartworm (dogs), and placed on a monthly preventative, in addition to other necessary treatments.

Adoption Center Hours:
Tuesday - Friday:: 12-6p.m.
Saturday:: 11-4p.m.

At FCHS, we commit to our animals; for this reason, all of our animals have a lifetime commitment from us. If an adoption does not work out, for any reason, we ask that all FCHS animals be returned to our facility.

animal.description:
XENA
Princess Warrior

Xena is the cutest little warrior princess you'll ever meet with a fiesty spirit that will win your heart quickly. Xena is house trained and great in her crate. Xena is good with most dogs with a proper introduction but would do best with bigger playful dogs. Xena spent her early days around cats and has been ok with her foster home’s guinea pigs.  Xena is a bit shy and takes a bit to warm up to new people, but once she decides your cool, then she loves you to pieces. We suggest that she goes to a home with older children, she can be a bit rambunctious with the little ones. She is a smart girl that loves to learn and has done well in training. We highly recommend that she continue with her training classes to help her blossom into the wonderful dog that she is. Xena is going to make some lucky person the Best Friend ever!  

Xena will always have some food restrictions and may require a little extra veterinary care over her lifetime, but she is otherwise expected to live a normal life. We spoke at length with our vet and spent some time determining if we should repair her cleft. In the end we decided that she is doing well with it and the dangers of the surgery were too great for her needs. Xena eats kibble out of a bowl and drinks out of a regular water dish. She does sneeze some of the water out and occasionally gets food stuck in her cleft, but she usually clears it herself. Xena can’t have any soft or wet foods. She must be kept on dry kibble. No canned or mushy foods, and no liquids other than water. She can have kibble, jerky-style treats, cooked meat, chews, etc.; just nothing with a goopy or liquid consistency that could cause her to aspirate. Plain water is fine. Her new family will need to watch and make sure Xena does not get anything stuck in her cleft that she cannot clear and keep an eye open for any infection.

Mateo is a sweet black and white american pitbull terrier mix. He's a little chunky at 92lbs and could do with some extra walks to get him into shape. animal.description:
Dear little Poppy is just 1-2 years old. 8-9 lbs, though she may need to gain weight.
Nice folks found her homeless; kept her a short while and then to B&B. Few days later she had three wee puppies. Only one lived beyond a couple of days....a little black/white boy....Muffin As of Thanksgiving, he is 8 weeks old and 1 pound! Poppy's milk dried up after just a few days, so Muffin has been bottle fed, then eye dropper and ultimately laps from a saucer. He's a demanding little squirt. We had to feed him every two hours round the clock - and this is not anywhere the first time B&B has chowed down on such a task.
We're not gonna show either of them until all their vaccines have been given...2021 Poppy will be spayed. If someone knocks us out with an application, we might consider a foster home. And this may not happen. Poppy and Muffin are doing just great here - they get a lot of attention from a variety of people and Poppy with other dogs, too. She is housetrained. We have no time to spend talking with folks who want them. Too much work to do and we are thin staffed. So, do not feel bad or upset if we do not respond to you. Move onto another dog in need. We update our web daily and are always rescuing doggies who become super companions.
In the meanwhile, you can email your application to B&B.
Please find our applications and valuable information under 'Adopt a dog'* on our website: *www.beaglesandbuddies.com* and email your application to beaglesandbuddies@gmail.com. Let us know your preference of appointment day/time and which dogs you are interested in and we will do our best to accommodate and email you the closest appointment available. Please allow us up to a week to get back to you. Most appointments will be Friday-Sunday, 10 am - 2 pm, for an hour.
*Note bring any other dog/s and the entire family to your meet and greet at B&B.* A complimentary training manual is included with each adoption, authored by terristeuben.com. Check out her website - she is fabulous!
B&B is glad to be open during the pandemic. We know the value and comfort of a loving pet companion and are doing our best to help the dogs and folks who need them. We update our website daily and are always rescuing, vetting, rehabilitating, socializing.
* We are accepting applications for volunteers to spend time with our dogs, hang out, sing/read to the shy ones, walk/toss ball with those who go to the playgrounds; cleaning, office work, gardening, and building/repair projects! *
Are you my furrever family?

For further info on the adoption process, please visit our home page and check out the "Adopt a Dog" section, which has thorough instructions. All our dogs are spayed/neutered, microchipped, and

fully vaccinated before adoption; they have been wormed, bathed, socialized, walked daily and much loved; each adoptee leaves with a leash, collar, and all medical records.

Our prices are higher than the shelters' because we nurse the dogs through their illnesses and get them needed surgeries and dentals. We also spend time socializing. Furthermore, unlike shelters, rescues do not get financial aid from the government and must rely on donations, grants, and adoption fees. Our fees for adults start at $150 and go up to $750. The higher end is for our most in demand dogs, such as young beagles and other purebred dogs. The lower end is for dogs who have been here a while. For puppies, we may go beyond this and charge $1000. The good news is that, because rescues fall under the "charity" category, the fees for our dogs are officially donations and are therefore tax deductible. You can think of it as donating to a worthy cause and getting a dog in return!

Sponsor Me

Beagles & Buddies must find ways to raise money so we can continue saving dogs. Your tax-deductible donation keeps our rescue kennel operating!

Hours

Friday: 10 am to 3 pm

Saturday: 10 am to 3 pm

Sunday: 10 am to 3 pm

Monday: CLOSED

Tuesday: CLOSED

Wednesday: CLOSED

Thursday: CLOSED



Weekday appointments may be available. We are a small staff and do our best to accommodate your needs. **Note that during COVID, we are not holding open houses on any day. Please email us for an appointment and include your application (found on our website, beaglesandbuddies.com, under "Forms"). Most appointments will be Friday through Sunday, though other days may also be available. We usually schedule one appointment per hour. Allow 1-2 hours for your appointment. Please look at our website and make a list of one or more dogs that you would like to see.

Contacting Us

If you have a question about adopting, giving up a dog, boarding, or volunteering, please visit the appropriate tabs on our
home page.

For more specific questions, call 626-444-9664 (please leave a voicemail if no answer) or email at beaglesandbuddies@gmail.com. Note that
Emailing
is always preferred!

Thanks!

Please note: If you are viewing this profile anywhere other than Beagles & Buddies own website, you are not receiving full info. Visit info on pet here.

animal.description:
We a proud to present to you the most beautiful and sweet-natured 3 yr-old German Shepherd girl named "PAIGE".

Summary: 
Paige is the sweetest girl that needs a new forever home as the only dog OR with smaller dogs due to 'hip dysplasia' and rough housing with other dogs could potentially hurt her hips! She is such a special girl who gets along with all dogs, is good with other animals AND adores children but needs a calmer environment to preserve her hips for the future! 

Backstory:
Paige was rescued from a puppy mill at 6-months old and was pregnant. Unfortunately she lost her puppy's and struggled giving birth. She was spayed immediately and has lived a happy life belonging to her original owners with two other doggy companions. 

Due to her doggy friends playing quite rough, Paige has needed to be separated from the others to protect her delicate hips. This has proved to be discomforting for her original owners, as Paige would love to play with her friends, but has to be constantly stopped due to her health conditions. 

Paige really is the pawfect dog!!:
- She really is as lovable and adoring as you see in the pictures!
- She does amazing with children and animals of all kind!
- Knows basic and some advance obedience!
- Is used to doing physical therapy (and all PT equipment would be included!)
- Is up-to-date on heart worm prevention and wears a Seresto collar. 
- Is eager to learn and please and is bursting with unconditional LOVE!

The future ahead:
In order to make sure her hips aren't worked too hard, Paige would need loving owners that could maintain her monthly injections and physical therapy to make sure this girl has a long and wonderful life!

Estimation of costs: 

1) Adequan injections - approximately $130 for 2 bottles. 
2 bottles = 6 months worth of injections. 

2) Glycoflex supplements - approximately $40 for a bag of 120. 
She gets one a day so the bag lasts for approximately 4 months.

3) Dasuquin supplements - approximately $45 for a bag of 84. 
At one chew a day, the bag lasts for just under 3 months. 

*A prescription is required for the Adequan injections, but is not necessary for the two supplements. 

Paige deserves a loving home where she will be cherished as a member of the family and has still has so much life and love to give! Please consider giving this precious girl another chance at life and she will reward you with unconditional love and loyalty! 

If you’d like more information or are interested in giving this precious girl a wonderful life, please text 4-6 photo's of your interior/exterior home and yard (including fence if applicable) to Judy (423-718-0939).

- - -

Please Note: Inquiries through Pet Finder may be slower to respond and the best form of communication/inquiry would be through text message at the number above. Thank you.

Search for "A PAW AND A PRAYER DOG RESCUE" on Facebook to see ALL our available dogs for adoption updated daily!

animal.description:
Location: Gloucester, VAHello there! My name is Daenerys. Those of you who are fans of "Game of Thrones" will know that I am named after the beautiful blond woman on that show. She is strong and beautiful and so am I. I was surrendered with my sister, Arya, through no fault of our own. I am the big sis, at 4 years old, and 77 pounds. Hey, more to love, right? I have a beautiful white coat, with just a couple patches of brown, one right on the top of my head! As you can see from my pictures, I am always smiling and am hoping to find myself my forever home. The nice folks at the pound say I appear to be housebroken, as I do my biz as soon as I go out the door. Sometimes I pull hard, as I am just so excited to go. I am a big strong girl, and so would like a big strong human to help me learn to be more patient. I have a harness which helps me too. And, of course, a big fenced in yard would be fun too, where we can all play together. I have lots of energy but would still like to be your couch buddy too.

Sadly, I am heartworm positive and have begun treatment, the cost being covered by the local humane society. Until my treatment is complete, a foster to adopt agreement would allow me to come live with you. Then the adoption would be finalized once my treatment is completed. I would love that as it would be so nice to go through this with my new loving family.

If you would like to know more about me and my sparkling personality, please contact my friend, Joyce. She is a volunteer here at the Gloucester Animal Control Pound and works with me everyday. She can be reached at 757-376-8360 or jemerson60@hotmail.com

Even tho I am at the pound, my adoption would be administered by the Gloucester Mathews Humane Society. To arrange a meet and greet or to apply to adopt me you can email to animalplacement@gmhumanesociety.org

Please come visit. I would love to meet you and maybe make you my new forever family! That would really make me smile!!
Gloucester County Animal Control
6584 Beehive Drive
Gloucester, VA 23061

animal.description:
DEXTER ~2-3 years old. Good with older considerate children and large dogs. Not good with small dogs or cats. Requires a fenced yard.

GSRA adopts to residents of VA, NC, and SC only

Hi, my name is Dexter, and I am 95lbs of pure friendly! I have heard German Shepherd Dogs can be aloof? I don't know the meaning of the word! In my three years on the planet, I have never met a person (including young people) I haven't liked! Of course, I can always like them better if they skritch me behind the ears!

Dexter is as loveable as he is good looking! He is house-broken, crate-trained, not a barker, will not get on furniture without invitation, does not mess with people food, does not jump up inappropriately, or pull on his leash. He entered our foster care with a crate, but swiftly earned 24hr. free roam of the house. He is calm and quiet through the night. He has had limited training, but is very smart and excited to learn new skills. His intense people-focus would make him a great candidate for advanced training with a motivated owner, but his outgoing personality makes him a poor choice as a watchdog. He needs daily moderate exercise (walks-he will Heel on lead) and could happily become a jogging buddy if invited. Dexter's tail has been docked following an episode of uncontrolled chewing. Food allergies are the suspected cause. He is currently on an anti-itch medication (Apoquel) and a restricted diet. Further evaluation to determine underlying causes will be indicated. Potential allergies may require ongoing management.

Dexter is usually a people-pleaser, but he does sometimes exhibit an independent streak. He also has a frisky side, and when he is feeling perky he tends to want to mouth dogs and people. He has excellent control and a gentle soul, but he is large and his playful mouthing could be misunderstood by some people or other dogs. He loves to rough-house when given the chance! Small dogs would be a poor fit. Given his size and occasional bursts of exuberance, he is not a good choice for homes with small children or unsteady seniors. Dexter has a strong prey drive, so no cats. He is great around strangers and good around most large dogs-but not all. Very occasionally he will meet a dog to whom he takes an instant dislike, so he needs some social supervision.

Dexter would do well as the only dog in a family who could give him a lot of attention and a sense of purpose. Someone working from home would be ideal. He would also be a lovely addition to a family of multiple dogs with compatible personalities. In either case, he really needs to be around people to thrive. He is a charming dog. It is hard to spend any time around him and not fall in love!

For more information on our adoptable pet list please visit: Adoptable Pet List

Please join us at our next Event(s):

Current Scheduled Events:

animal.description:
Eddie is just the sweetest youngster! He had a fairly severe heart problem but has been treated by the Cardiology Dept at MU Vet Hospital. His long term prognosis is excellent! (See below)

He loves everyone and every critter he meets! He'd love to come meet you too if you love playing and then snoozing on the couch!!!

History of heart condition: His treatment was January 13, 2021 and He has a follow up appointment set for mid April.

Upon further testing at MU Veterinary Health Center, it was confirmed through Echocardiogram that Eddie has Pulmonic Stenosis (PS), categorized at moderate to severe. Patients with that degree have the potential to develop complications such as exercise intolerance, collapse, arrhythmias and congestive heart failure.

Eddie is a good candidate for Balloon Valvuloplasty (BVP), which is a minimally invasive, palliative surgical procedure that reduces the degree of PS, along with the risk of future complications.

We are currently raising funds so that Eddie can receive the much needed surgery to live his life to the fullest as someones best friend and loyal companion.

In order to qualify for ALIVE Rescue Memphis's program all of the following steps must be met:

 •You must be at least 21 years of age and be able to provide ALIVE with proof of age.

 •Any current pets must be up to date on vaccinations, and be spayed/neutered. Exceptions to this will only be considered if proof of a medical explanation is provided.

 •If you currently rent, you must provide a landlord’s phone number and a copy of your executed lease.

 •All members of the family living in the home where the animal will be placed must be interviewed.

 •Applicant must live within 50 miles of Memphis if interested in adopting and within 30 miles of Memphis if interested in fostering. 

 •Allow an ALIVE Rescue Memphis representative into your home for a visit to insure that your home is safe for the potential new pet.  

  •You must allow an ALIVE Rescue Memphis representative into your home for a visit to ensure that your home is safe for the potential new pet. 

  •You must be able and willing to spend the time and money necessary to provide training, medical treatment, and proper care for a pet.

  •Currently, adoptions fees in Memphis are $275 for a dog over 4 months of age, $300 for a dog under 4 months of age. 

  •We require an additional $75 training deposit at the time of adoption. You will be required to enroll and complete a training class with your new companion at one of our approved training facilities. Once ALIVE Rescue Memphis receives proof of the completed class, this $75 deposit will be refunded.

animal.description:
OLIVER is a sweetheart. He was born with craniosynostosis (human babies get this as well) - it just means that when the soft skull bones were growing, they grew in a slightly asymmetrical line. In Oliver's case, it just created an absolutely adorable face. He's healthy in every other way and it doesn't bother him and other pets don't notice. He's just gets more hugs :-) 

He is robustly affectionate and immensely loves back scratches. He loves to give kisses! He gets a huge smile on his face when he plays with his puppy girls (two six month old puppies, one of whom is deaf). It's "tongue-out-Tuesday" all day whenever he gets to play with them. And they love him too! He tolerates them jumping all over him and kissing him :-)

He is house trained, crate trained, neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, and about 5yrs old.

We have specific adoption and Covid rules listed below.

Revised adoption policy
Due to Covid -19 pandemic and social distancing requirements, we've revised our adoption policy. 
First, please email (desertpawsnm@gmail.com) to inquire before you fill out the online application. (Please do not call or text). 

We are unable to do multi-dog/cat meetgreets or adoption events at this time or bring multiple animals to your house to choose from, so please only inquire if you're serious about adopting this particular animal. If you're just shopping around with several shelters and rescues, please let us know this. 

If your application is approved (which "could" take up to one week) then we will contact you to set up a Zoom chat or ph call to answer questions/clarify anything and set up a day/time to bring the pet to you. 

Since we can't come into the home/yard due to Covid-19, we ask that you send us pics /video of your home/yard/living area/current pets. 

We will discuss with you about meeting your other pets. At the meeting/adoption at your house (outside) please wear a mask (as will we), keep to a properly distanced social distance and have hand sanitizer and your own leash.

We adopt locally to Central Abq, Santa Fe, Los Alamos and Rio Rancho. No out of area adoptions inquiries please. No young children for our adoptions please. Please consider adopting one of Oliver's "puppy girls" with him! (Daisy who's deaf and Folie).

The animals are fostered and our foster families like to know their fosters are happy, healthy, and cared for during their lifetime. We appreciate staying in touch periodically (just a pic, holiday card, social media, pics/videos  etc will do :-)

Our volunteers and adoption board are working diligently with an overload of inquiries since Covid to match families and forever pets. We're sorry, but if you email us with questions that are already answered here or fill out an application that does not fit the parameters of our procedures we will not be replying to you. Thank you for your understanding on this!

Thank you - we look forward to hearing from you!

animal.description:
Elias is a 4 year old Bull Terrier mix, about 60 pounds. He previously lived and got along well with a female senior dog, two cats and a bearded dragon. He also loved the family, including two children but has come back to SAAP to find a new home.

Elias is very sweet and loves all the snuggles and attention he can get (at least when he's awake). He rides great in the car, and is house and crate trained.

He gets around like a champ (jumps in and out of the car, runs up and down stairs, plays with other dogs) but has some pain in his back left knee that can cause him to give a warning bark/nip if he is startled while sleeping or if it is touched when he doesn't expect it--no reports of ever making contact/biting a human or pet. He has seen a vet who recommends pain medicine as needed, but surgery isn't necessary. He would need a family who can give him space to feel safe and relax.

animal.description:
Sheldon, not unlike his namesake, is basically an theorectical physicist. He likes routine, he thrives on intellectual challenges, he likes to know what's happening and when it's happening. If you're an experienced dog owner with your sights set on a dog who will excel at being your exercise partner and especially if you're interested in a dog to train for agility or Fast CAT, then keep reading!
Not first time dog owner (non negotiable)
You are on a regular schedule with work
No children (in a few years, sure. But at first, Shelly is looking to build a relationship with you)
Someone who knows shepherds/working dogs
Connects with dogs who are social and enjoy a high energy dog
Would do well with a mentor pup as a dog partner that still has lots of energy and patient for playtime 
Cats? He’s curious but we haven’t seen him interact - likely not ideal
Super active person - not (2) 15-min walks a day, we mean hiking, running, maybe even parkour!
“Special Talents”

	?	Crate-trained!
	?	Knows all hiking commands - will sit for treats, “down,” shake (both hands), “gimme a kiss,” “high five” and waits for his “ok” command to eat, get a treat, start his enrichment game, come inside the house, etc.
	?	Basic click training 
	?	Never had ONE potty accident in the crate or inside the house ??
	?	4 weeks of premium boarding and training with Nashville K-9 - graduated with honors and especially loved agility course trainings 
	?	Can jump 8 ft in the air - incredibly agile 
	?	Loves pupsicles!
	?	Loves bubbles!
	?	Super smart
	?	Handsome
	?	Great “nose”
	?	Always aware and on alert 
	?	Big bark - security 

The “boring stuff” 

Fully vaccinated, scheduled to be neutered 12/4. Application is required and while you may be an awesome person, if you don't meet the necessary wish list Sheldon has articulated, then please understand we aren't able to entertain your inquiry. To apply to adopt Sheldon, fill out this super easy link: http://bit.ly/EastCAN_Application

animal.description:
Seeking foster to adopt while we finish the treatment on his foot

Age: Approx 1.5 years old
Location: Calgary
Breed: Husky, GSD X
Sex: Neutered male
Weight: 50 lbs
Energy: High
Health Notes: Cody has a foot injury that we are treating. RDDR is covering this treatment for him. His new person may need to do some bandaging and washing of his wound.
Cats: NO
Dogs: Yes- But if he is going to to live with another dog, this dog should be extremely playful as well.
Kids: Over 13 please due to Cody’s size and energy
Adoption fee: $475

Meet Cody!

This young fellow is full of energy, life, and love! Cody has had quite the journey coming into care, and is currently recovering from a trauma to his foot. This medical challenge has not stopped him from being a happy and friendly guy. In other words, this hiccup is not holding him back from being a young, energetic dog.

Cody is enjoying life inside a home very, very much and loves all the comforts that come along with it including stuffy toys, especially if they squeak! He has caught on to housetraining quickly and sleeps through the night like a champ. We have introduced him to crate training and this is being done a little bit each day. He has quickly mastered sit, and we are working on other cues and finding good ways for him to work out his husky- mix energy. Cody is currently living with two older dogs who refuse to play with him despite his repeated efforts. He has been friendly with dogs met while on walks. Leash training is ongoing, and considering he did not know a leash, collar, or a harness prior to coming into Rosier's care he is doing very well.

Cody needs a home with a yard, and a person who is active. Walking, running, hiking....Cody would love all of it. Cody requires daily physical and mental exercise and will need a committed family.

We recommend kids 13 yrs of age and older as Cody can play hard and is still learning to not play with his mouth.

Cody will thrive as the only dog with all of the attention, he could live with another large and playful dog. Cody has a lot of love to share and is looking for his furever home.


If you are interested in adopting Cody, please fill out an adoption application at www.rosierdays.com/adopt

The application must be submitted and reviewed before a meet and greet will be arranged.

Please be patient in waiting to hear back from us as the dogs care is our priority and all of our volunteers work as well as run the rescue in their spare time. You should hear from us within 72 hours.

animal.description:
Meet Henry! This spunky fellow is just over one year and weighs 35 pounds. He has high white socks on his front legs--like a pro basketball player! He is working on proper leash skills and doing super. He would really love a yard to chase a ball around in. With his tail wagging and his ears flopping, he is one happy pup when he runs! Henry enjoys meeting new people and playing with the foster family's resident dogs. Henry would do best with kids over 10 as he is working really hard on learning not to jump in excitement. Henry loves sleeping on his dog bed and curls up into a content and lovable ball as he snoozes. When his family is in the kitchen, he sets up shop on the mat in front of the sink. Whoever does the dishes needs to step around him--he just wants to be close to his pet parents. Henry's new family must be committed to his continued training-he is eager to learn more and is super smart This pup would make a perfect pup for an active household, tweens, and a yard!  Henry is house broken and crate trained and ready to go home to his very own family.  

Henry is neutered, heartworm negative and up to date on age appropriate core vaccines. Adoption fee is $350. As with all rescue animals, breed determination cannot be validated without genetic testing. Visit www.tinymiraclesrescue.org and click on the APPLY tab for an overview of Tiny Miracles adoption process. Thanks for adopting and saving a life -- you are Henry's hero!

I love to go for nice walks around the neighborhood, and I love love love to go out to the yard and sniff around. I'm an introvert and independent type so sniffing and exploring are my kind of fun. After LOTS of sniffing I'm always ready for attention so I'll go to my hooman for some petting. I'm a sensitive guy and like gentle petting. I don't care too much for toys but sometimes I get excited and feel a little frisky so I will pick up my ball and start playing. I like to play case the ball then run away with it. It's so much fun!! I enjoy other doggy companions but would like to meet my new friend first. Once inside I like to chill out, and enjoy some quiet time. Right now I'm learning to lay in this thing called a crate. I'm training hardright now I'm working on crate training, housetraining and learning to sit. Training is not my favorite thing to do. The hoomans over here say that I would require a patient trainer who has plenty of creativity and uses positive training methods. because remember I'm a sensitive guy. I'm very devoted and protective of my family but I can be reserved and aloof around strangers. The hoomans at the shelter say I'm a great guy and mild mannered. While I like it here at the shelter boy, would I be excited to find my forever hooman! We can sit around and watch some Lobo Basketball and go for walks in the sun. Wouldn't that be fun?! Stop into the Westside Shelter to meet me, I sure would like to meet you. Weight: 76lbs Housetrained: no but working on it Dogs: good but would need a meet and greet Cats: Unknown Children: Over 14 years old due to Handling sensitivity, afraid of fast movements and certain type of touch

MEET HAZE!

HAZE is one of our volunteer favorites here in the rescue family!

Our HAZE was found abandoned in a park where he was tied to a tree!  It was one of the saddest cases we have come across as this five year old boy is super loveable and adores all people!

HAZE is housebroken.  He will need his person to continue to teach him how to walk on his leash as he is strong and tends to pull more than walk while outdoors. HAZE would do best as your one and only fur baby in the home as he has not had much exposure to other dogs and does not know how to respect physical boundaries while walking.

HAZE is not a fan of cats so he can not have one as his roommate.

Are you ready to give HAZE the FUREVER home that he deserves? If so, please email Forblakessakerescue@gmail.com to complete an application!

Apply at: http://www.plannedpethood.org/adopt/available-dogs.html

Charlotte might be one of the prettiest pups you ever meet. Golden blonde fur, sweet brown eyes and a wonderful smile. Charlotte is energetic and smart. She warms up to new people right away and wants to be a human’s best friend. 

Charlotte loves car rides, she loves to play, she adores adventures outdoors. But there is one thing Charlotte cannot seem to love: other dogs. Charlotte needs to be the only canine in her home. She tolerates walking past other leashed dogs at the park and at the vet but Charlotte displays guarding tendencies and a strong discomfort being around dogs in close proximity. Charlotte needs a family who understands her feelings towards other dogs and is willing to make her feel safe and comfortable. 

Charlotte has been working on manners while being fostered at Central Kennels. We would like to have Charlotte attend follow up training to assist her new family as she settles into her home. If you would like to meet or adopt Charlotte, please complete our application. Please note that Charlotte would be best as the only pet in a home.  Her adoption fee is sponsored!

Please understand the statements about this animal are based upon the foster home's evaluation of the animal.  The animal might behave differently (negatively or positively) in your home.  While the animal might be good with the current foster’s dogs, cats, children, etc., it may not be with your animal(s) or children.  The animal may be housebroken or litter trained in the home of the foster but may relapse in your home.  The animal is represented to the public as it performs in the foster home and any statements made regarding the animal are conditional to that foster home setting.  Those interested in adopting should have read all information about the animal and understand they cannot claim they did not understand the facts about this animal as understood by Planned Pethood and/or the foster.  Planned Pethood and vet(s) do our best to provide accurate age and breed of the animal, but sometimes they are educated guesses.  Please understand that statements made regarding this animal are simply overviews and are not guaranteed.  Your adoption fee is non-refundable for any reason.

,Due to COVID-19, all adoptions will be by appointment only. To adopt, complete our online adoption application and an Adoption Counselor will contact you within 48-hours to schedule your adoption appointment. Adoptions for any pets in foster will be completed offsite at our PetSmart Claiborne location on a case by case basis. The safety of our foster parents and community is of utmost importance to us and it will be at the foster's discretion if they'd like to meet at this time. Thank you for choosing adoption! 

Watson is a wise soul among dogs.  He came from rough beginnings and worked his way up the ranks to Dog Detective.  He sacrificed a lot including having a family in order to pursue his career.  Watson ended up burning out after the case of French Quarter Rats 2020 and came to us needed a mental health vacation.  He has spent a lot of time working on himself and is now in a place to love again.  He gets along with dogs and cats and while he can be a little aloof, he really enjoys close knit families.  His fur is the softest this side of the Mississippi river.  While he has some health issues he doesn't complain and he has a bright future ahead of him.  Please think of welcoming this mellow fella into your home in 2021.


To inquire about an adoptable animal from the Louisiana SPCA, please call 504.368.5191, ext. 150 to speak with an adoption counselor.
To see more adoptable animals from the Louisiana SPCA, please go to http://la-spca.org/adopt.



The petfinder.com system requires that we choose a predominant breed or breed mix for our dogs. Visual breed identification in dogs is unreliable so for most of the dogs we are only guessing at predominant breed or breed mix. We get to know each dog as an individual and will do our best to describe each of our dogs based on personality, not by breed label.

animal.description:
Welcome Dahlia! This precious 4-year-old pup weighs in around 35 pounds. She finished raising her litter of 8 beautiful babies, and she did such a wonderful job being a good mama and watching all of them grow up and join their forever families. Now, she is ready to find her own, and we can’t think of a pup more deserving of a loving family than this little angel!

She is already housebroken and completely crate-trained. Dahlia lets dad know when it’s time for a potty break by waiting patiently by the door. Since becoming an empty-nester, Dahlia has bloomed into a well-behaved, independent woman. She knows how to sit, lie down, leave it, and wait on command. She’s also working on “focus” and will have that down in no time. 

Dahlia is happy to play with other dogs or do her own thing, depending on her options. However she is more accepting of other dogs if she can have a slow, structured introduction. Dahlia can entertain herself with toys or exploring in the backyard solo. In addition to being able to befriend any canine sibling, Dahlia is also cat-friendly. Dogs just don’t come much more flexible than this girl! 

Dahlia loves to get one-on-one attention from her humans, and she is perfectly content to lay around and have a lazy day with the family if that’s what’s on the agenda. That being said, she does get her occasional bout of zoomies, and she loves to spend time outside in the fresh air. When Dahlia gets really excited, she loves to pick up her toys and show them off to anyone who will look.

This mama absolutely loves anyone that comes along her path, and from the moment she meets a new person, she wants to be their new best friend. When you are sitting down, she’ll crawl into your lap and invite herself for all the snuggles she can get, but if you’re standing, it’s a bit more challenging for her to figure out how to cuddle up (but that doesn’t mean she won’t try!). Even though she’s a snuggler, she also understands that her people can’t be around her all the time, and she can entertain herself with a chew toy when people are busy or need some space. 

Like so many mamas out there, Dahlia is patient, forgiving, and always looking to make those around her smile, and she is SO GOOD at it. She has done a wonderful job focusing on her babies, but it’s time to let this mom get pampered and put herself first! Could she be the perfect addition to your family? Contact us today!
 


If you’d like to be considered to adopt, the first step in the process is to submit an application through our website: http://athenscaninerescue.com/adoption-procedures/. Our adoption fee is $250 per dog over the age of 6 months and $300 per dog 6 months or younger. We accept payment by Venmo, PayPal, or card.

This includes: basic vet care (i.e. basic vaccinations, including boosters completed after adoption, spay/neuter, heartworm/flea preventatives, and treatment for any health needs while in our care), a microchip, a week’s worth of food for the trial-period, and a harness lead.

We typically adopt to homes within 30 minutes of Athens, GA, as we require a basic home check to ensure all dogs are placed in a safe environment. If you are further away than that and are interested in one of our pups, please still fill out an application and we can discuss your options. WE ARE CURRENTLY NOT ACCEPTING OUT OF STATE APPLICATIONS. 

We do not have a facility and operate through a network of foster homes. Thus, we do not have a phone number. If you’d like to discuss potential adoptions, please email at adopt@athenscaninerescue.com.

Summer is an absolute gem of a dog and not only loves to run and play, but will happily climb into your lap for some cuddle time as well. Although not required, Summer gets along wonderful with other male dogs and would love a social male dog in her new home too.

While Summer is all-around wonderful, she is going to need a family that is prepared to give her some space when she arrives at home to decompress and settle in. Once she has had proper time to settle in, she will surely show you her fun and loving side and she will surely win you over! Summer is a smart girl who would love a home that is willing to do fun puzzle games or toys with her too, or maybe even some new tricks and let her use her brain. Summer would also make a great adventure buddy, as she is not overly energetic but still has plenty of energy to join you on hikes or trips to the beach.

animal.description:
Hi there!  My name is Schultz!   For some reason, my former owner left me all on my own. I don't know why because I try to be a good boy.  I was really scared and boy, was I ever happy when a nice human came along and took me to this great foster home where I’m getting plenty of TLC.  I had heart worms and some other infections, but the nice rescue folks made sure I got the treatment I needed and now I’m a happy, healthy boy all set to hang my leash with my forever family.

I’m 2 years old and weigh 75 pounds.  They tell me I'm a black lab mix, maybe with collie, but that's a best guess..  My foster dad says that whatever my breed mix is, I am a very loving boy.  I do like to please my humans.  I enjoy all kind of toys…balls, sticks – you name it – I like to play with it.  I also love water!  It’s so much fun when my foster dad sprays me with a hose.  I still have plenty of puppy energy so an active family that will take me on hikes and walks would be perfect for me.  There are no children in my foster home, but I know I would enjoy living with older kids -  about 12 or over.  I would never be mean to any kids but, I wouldn't  want to overwhelm the younger set with my playful self.

I’m fully crate trained and working on my house training.  I was an outside dog before, but with a regular routine and positive reinforcement, I’ve been learning my inside manners and will have them down.  I still need some practice walking on a leash, but I'm sure my new family will continue to work with me on that, too.  I prefer a slow introduction to other dogs, but once I get to know them, we get along fine. Cat are not for me.  I'd love it if someone is with me during the day. I think I would get lonely by myself. And, if my home has a fenced yard, that would be perfect! 

I’ve been neutered and I’m up to date on my vaccines.  I even have a cool thing called a micro-chip.  I’m not perfect yet, but if you have the time to spend with me, I promise to try real hard to become the best dog I can be.  If you’d like an application to adopt me, please email Chris at rescue3@earthlink.net for an application and she’ll send one right out. My adoption fee is $375.  Can’t wait to meet you! 

Like us on Facebook at www. facebook.com/pawsclawsnewengland
Follow/tag us on Instagram: @pawsclawsne or #pawsclawsne

animal.description:
YOU MUST HAVE AN APPROVED APPLICATION IN ORDER TO MEET OUR PETS.

Bentley is a cute little 10 year old who was pulled from a county shelter by LPIA. We do not know his history. He seems to be a non or low shedding breed, maybe a Shih Tzu or Lhaso Apso mix?

Foster mom says he is a happy guy and a good companion, just prefers gentle, respectful handling on his own terms and at a slow pace. He would not appreciate small children and their sudden moves or grabbiness.

He does need time to acclimate to a new home, surroundings, routine and family.

Bentley loves to play with toys though he mostly prefers just hanging out. He walks well on a leash (short walks are all he needs), is well behaved on car rides, and sleeps all night. He seems to be good about baths, gentle brushing and having his nails trimmed.

He has been fine with the other dogs and cats in his current foster home but is not one to play with other dogs. He should be fine with low key dogs that will not pester him.

He loves eating and has not shown any food or toy possessiveness. But, if he is being naughty and has something new in his mouth that he should not, he can feel possessive (he will happily trade for a good treat!).

He will bark when he wants something or wants to be with you and cannot see you, so he is best in a house setting instead of an apartment. He likes to know where you are and be able to see you. However, his foster mom leaves him in a baby gated kitchen when she goes out and he is usually just sleeping when she returns.

Bentley loves to be in the same space with his people and he would happily hang outside in a fenced yard with you all day! He loves outside and would be a lovely companion while you are gardening or just relaxing outside.

He is working on his housetraining and does have some old man dribbles at times. He  will happily wear a belly band in his new home to prevent accidents. 

He will need some time to adapt to a new home and potty routine and will definitely need to wear his belly band during that adjustment period. You will need several so that they can be changed and washed routinely.

An absorbent pad under his bedding would keep his doggie bed or crate nice and dry.

Bentley has been sleeping happily in a crate at night and even puts himself in it if he feels ready for bedtime before you. He likes to wake up slowly in the morning and lets you know when he is ready to wake up and got out to potty.

He is not a fan of being held and snuggled (this could be a back/ribs/knee discomfort or pain issue), but is fine with being gently picked up when needed. 

He eats dry kibble but really prefers wet food mixed in the dry.

His back legs tend to splay out at times and an X-ray showed an old injury.  He has a heart murmur and some skin issues that should resolve with continued good quality food and treatment. He has diminished hearing and sight so may not hear commands but he eats well and responds to treats.

We are really hoping that Bentley will find a great new quiet, adults only home that will celebrate his many good qualities and understand the special needs of a senior pup. Every dog deserves a happy home, especially seniors!

Please submit your application so that you can set up an appointment to meet Bentley and see if he is the one for you!

Adoption donation $175.

Please note that we do not ship animals. We also require a home visit before finalizing any adoptions so preference is given to applicants within a 90 mile range. You will be required to come to High Point, NC to meet/pick up your new pet.

HOW TO APPLY:
1. Go to www.lovingpetinnadoptions.org
2. Click on the "Adoption Application" link on the left side of the page.
3. The application will open as a PDF and you should have the ability to fill it in from that page. Be sure to complete all fields.
4. Save the application to your computer, then attach in an email and send to petprojectnc@gmail.com
5. Someone will review your application as soon as possible, usually within 24 hours, and will be in touch with next steps.

animal.description:
Hello Humans Hank aka HAM SAMICH here (cause I be a silly and goofy boy) and I am still SINGLE and ready to pack my bags and move in with YOU!

I am a big beefy delicious boy who was dumped in a bad area and left alone in the cold to fend for myself!
I was sooooo scared and freaked out and no one could get near me, until someone called this rescue and they got in the car and hotfooted it to get me before something even worse than being abandoned with no food or shelter happened to me! 

I went for training and am now in a temporary foster home until I find the right human to make me a part of their LOVING life.

I'm a 75 pound 4 year old GORGEOUS American Bully and I'm good with other dogs but would be best with a balanced female doggo my size or as your one and ONLY, I'd love to get all of the LOVE from YOU! 
NO cats or small dogs-sorry I like to chase them too much.

I'm house and crate trained, I know lots of commands, great on leash and am a total goofball who loves walks, car rides, adventures and I even LOVE GETTING A BATH!

I do need someone with previous bully experience who can give me structure and consistency. I'm SMART and a super fast learner! 
An adult only home is perfect for me, no kids cause I might knock them over by accident. 


Please head on over to www.bulliesandbuddies.com to fill out an adoption application if you think we are a good fit ok?

Love, HAM SAMICH aka Handsome Hank 

I am in the Southern CA area-sorry but my rescue does NOT adopt out of state
